Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.00,0:00:10.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\c&H00FFFF&}字幕转制｜{\b1\c&HFFFFFF&}天外生物\N{\b0\c&H079FFF&}感谢原字幕制作者
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.70,0:01:42.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,300)\fs120\fsp8\fscx80\shad5\4a&H33&\pos(975,690)}爱在日落黄昏时
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.22,0:01:59.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,《此时》\N读者见面会\N作者\N杰西·华莱士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.60,0:02:02.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,你认为这本书算自传式的吗？\N{\rENG}Do you consider the book to be autobiographical?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.64,0:02:05.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个…\N{\rENG}Well, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.88,0:02:08.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,…什么书不是自传式的呢？\N{\rENG}...isn't everything autobiographical?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.88,0:02:13.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们都是通过自己那小小的钥匙孔看外面的世界，对吧？\N{\rENG}I mean, we all see the world through our own tiny keyhole, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.55,0:02:15.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，我总想起汤玛斯·沃尔夫说的\N{\rENG}I mean, I always think of Thomas Wolfe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.65,0:02:20.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看过《天使望故乡》那本书前面那短短一页的“致读者”吗？\N{\rENG}Have you ever seen that little one-page " Note to Reader" in the front of Look Homeward, Angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.19,0:02:21.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我在说什么吧？\N{\rENG}Well, you know what I'm talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.99,0:02:26.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,总之，他说我们的生命就是由点点滴滴集合而成的\N{\rENG}Anyway, he says that we are the sum of all the moments of our lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.10,0:02:30.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而任何人坐下来，写出来的都不过是自己生命中的体验…\N{\rENG}...and that anybody who sits down to write will use the clay of their own life...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.07,0:02:32.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,…谁都无法回避\N{\rENG}...that you can't avoid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.77,0:02:37.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以当我审视我的人生，我必须得承认，我发现…\N{\rENG}So when I look at my own life,you konw I have to admit, right, that I...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.97,0:02:42.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我从来没有经历过枪林弹雨或是暴力事件，起码没真正体验过\N{\rENG}I've never been around a bunch of guns or violence, you know, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.68,0:02:46.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有什么政治阴谋，也没什么直升机失事\N{\rENG}No political intrigue or a helicopter crash, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.25,0:02:51.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我的人生，从我个人观点来看仍然是富有戏剧性的\N{\rENG}But my life, from my own point of view,has been full of drama, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.95,0:02:54.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,于是我想也许我也能写本书…\N{\rENG}And so I thought,if I could write a book...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.62,0:02:59.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,…记录下我见到某人时的感觉\N{\rENG}...that could capture what it's like to really meet somebody...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.26,0:03:01.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，我经历过的最刺激的事情之一\N{\rENG}One of the most exciting things that's happened to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.10,0:03:04.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,…就是真正和某人见面，让两个人心灵相通\N{\rENG}...is to meet somebody,make that connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.60,0:03:08.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,而如果我能把它表现出来…你明白吗，抓住那一刻的感觉…\N{\rENG}And if I could make that valuable,you know, to capture that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.31,0:03:12.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,…那就是我的写作意图了，亦或者…\N{\rENG}...that would be the attempt, or....
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.14,0:03:15.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,你满意我的回答吗？\N{\rENG}Did I answer your question?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.21,0:03:18.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我干脆就直说吧…\N{\rENG}I'll try to be more specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.12,0:03:21.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在火车上遇见一个年轻的法国女郎\N{\rENG}Was there ever a French young woman on a train you met...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.98,0:03:24.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,并和她共度良宵\N{\rENG}...and spent an evening with?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.19,0:03:31.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个，对我来说…我是说…\N{\rENG}See, to me, that.... I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.29,0:03:34.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,- …这并不重要，你懂吗？ - 就是说的确有了？\N{\rENG}- ...that's not important, you know?  - So that's a yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:39.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，既然我人在法国，这又是我签名售书的最后一站，那就算有吧\N{\rENG}All right, since I'm in France and this is the last stop of my book tour, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.47,0:03:42.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.47,0:03:45.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,华莱士先生，这本书的结尾给我们留下了悬念\N{\rENG}Mr. Wallace, the book ends on an ambiguous note.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.04,0:03:47.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们不知道\N{\rENG}We don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.58,0:03:50.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,你认为他们六个月之后会重聚吗？\N{\rENG}Do you think they get back together in six months...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:53.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像他们彼此承诺的那样？\N{\rENG}...Iike they promise each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.45,0:03:56.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,像他们保证的？\N{\rENG}Like they promised?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.95,0:04:00.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我认为这个问题实际上是，是个…\N{\rENG}I think how you answer that,you know, is....
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.49,0:04:04.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,是个很好的测试，看看你到底是喜欢浪漫还是对它嗤之以鼻\N{\rENG}It's a good test, right,if you're a romantic or a cynic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.99,0:04:08.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，你认为他们会重聚的，对吧？\N{\rENG}Right? I mean, you think they get back together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.17,0:04:10.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 显然你并不这么认为  - 是的\N{\rENG}- You don't, for sure.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.87,0:04:12.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,还是你希望他们会，不过你无法肯定\N{\rENG}And you hope they do,but you're not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.07,0:04:16.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 所以你才问这个问题  - 你认为他们会重聚吗？\N{\rENG}- That's why you're asking the question.  - Do you think they get back together?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.97,0:04:19.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说你们重聚了吗？在现实生活中？\N{\rENG}I mean, did you in real life?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.54,0:04:22.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,现实生活中…？\N{\rENG}Did I in real...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.75,0:04:25.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,要用我祖父的话来说啊\N{\rENG}Look, in the words of my grandfather, okay:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.51,0:04:28.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,天晓得会不会\N{\rENG}"To answer that would take the piss out of the whole thing."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.52,0:04:33.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们的时间只够问最后一个问题了\N{\rENG}We just have the time for one last question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.22,0:04:34.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,你下一本书将是什么？\N{\rENG}What is your next book?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:40.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道，老兄，我真的不知道…\N{\rENG}I don't know, man. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.26,0:04:43.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一直…一直在考虑这个构思…\N{\rENG}I've been...I've been thinking about this....
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.90,0:04:46.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,我总是想写本书…\N{\rENG}Well, I always kind of wanted to write a book...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.77,0:04:50.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,…一切都发生在一首流行歌曲那么长时间内\N{\rENG}...that all took place within the space of a pop song.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:53.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,总共大概三到四分钟吧\N{\rENG}Like three or four minutes long,the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.01,0:04:57.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,整个故事大概是说有个男人…\N{\rENG}The story, the idea,is that there's this guy, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.71,0:05:00.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,…他非常的沮丧，因为…\N{\rENG}...and he's totally depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.62,0:05:04.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,他最大的梦想就是拥有一段轰轰烈烈的爱情，一次冒险…\N{\rENG}His great dream was to be a lover,an adventurer, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.95,0:05:07.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,…比如开着摩托周游南美\N{\rENG}...riding motorcycles through South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.92,0:05:10.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是事实上他只是坐在大理石桌前吃着龙虾\N{\rENG}And instead he's sitting at a marble table eating lobster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.83,0:05:13.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,他有份不错的工作，妻子也很漂亮\N{\rENG}He's got a good job and a beautiful wife, right, but that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.10,0:05:17.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,他应有尽有，但是这并不是他真正想要的…\N{\rENG}Everything that he needs.But that doesn't matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.67,0:05:20.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,…因为他真正想要的是为某种理想而战\N{\rENG}...because what he wants is to fight for meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.90,0:05:23.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,你明白吗，快乐来自于过程\N{\rENG}You know? Happiness is in the doing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:25.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,而不是因为你得到了你想要的东西\N{\rENG}Not in the getting what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.84,0:05:29.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,总之，他坐在那里，突然间…\N{\rENG}So he's sitting there,and just that second...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.55,0:05:33.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,…他五岁的小女儿跳上了桌子\N{\rENG}...his little 5-year-old daughter hops up on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.95,0:05:37.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,他知道她该下来，因为她可能会受伤\N{\rENG}And he knows that she should get down, because she could get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.45,0:05:42.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是她正穿着夏日的裙子随着那首歌翩翩起舞\N{\rENG}But she's dancing to this pop song in a summer dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.79,0:05:44.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后一晃眼\N{\rENG}And he looks down...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.99,0:05:47.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,…突然间，他回到了十六岁\N{\rENG}...and all of a sudden, he's 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.33,0:05:53.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,他的高中女友正送他回家\N{\rENG}And his high-school sweetheart is dropping him off at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:05:57.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,而他们刚刚度过了他们的初夜，她很爱他…\N{\rENG}And they just lost their virginity,and she loves him...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.71,0:06:01.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而汽车收音机里里播放着的是同样的一首曲子\N{\rENG}...and the same song is playing on the car radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.94,0:06:04.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后她爬上了车顶，开始在那里跳舞\N{\rENG}And she climbs up and starts dancing on the roof of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.11,0:06:06.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,这一下，他开始很担心她！\N{\rENG}And now he's worried about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.82,0:06:11.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,她很美，表情也竟然和她女儿一模一样\N{\rENG}And she's beautiful, with a facial expression just like his daughter's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.45,0:06:13.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,事实上，这可能就是他为什么会喜欢她的原因\N{\rENG}In fact, maybe that's why he even likes her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.82,0:06:16.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗，他知道他并不是身处回忆之中…\N{\rENG}You see, he knows he's not remembering this dance...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.96,0:06:20.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而是他就在那里，他同时出现在人生的两个场景之中\N{\rENG}...he's there. He's there,in both moments, simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.86,0:06:24.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,就在这一瞬间，他全部的人生好像都交汇到了一起\N{\rENG}And just for an instant,all his life is just folding in on itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.50,0:06:27.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,对他来说，时间明显是个谎言\N{\rENG}And it's obvious to him that time is a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.51,0:06:31.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为那一刻将一直延伸下去…\N{\rENG}That it's all happening all the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.14,0:06:35.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而且每个时刻之内都包含着另一个时刻…\N{\rENG}...and inside every moment is another moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.98,0:06:37.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,…一切的一切，都发生在同一瞬间\N{\rENG}...all happening simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.01,0:06:41.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,总之，这就是我大概的想法，总之\N{\rENG}Anyway, that's kind of the idea.Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:44.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们的作者很快就得去机场了…\N{\rENG}Our author has to be going to the airport soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.02,0:06:47.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,…那么，谢谢各位今天下午光临\N{\rENG}...so thank you all very much for coming over this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.16,0:06:51.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,尤其要感谢华莱士先生和我们共度了这么美好的一个下午\N{\rENG}And a special thanks to Mr. Wallace for being with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.63,0:06:53.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢，谢谢\N{\rENG}Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:55.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,希望你出下本书的时候我们还能在这见到你！\N{\rENG}We hope to see you here again with your next book.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.95,0:06:58.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}感谢大家光临\N{\rENG}Merci a toutes et a tous qu'etre venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.05,0:07:01.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}我们为大家准备了香槟和一些小点心\N{\rENG}Comme vous voyez y a du champagne,y a des petites choses a gagnoter,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.55,0:07:02.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}请尽情享受吧\N{\rENG}donc servez vous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:05.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢各位，我必须在几点之前去机场？\N{\rENG}Thank you all. How much longer before I have to go to the airport?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.04,0:07:07.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，你必须在七点半之前离开？\N{\rENG}Oh, you should leave at 7:30...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.91,0:07:10.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 最迟七点半！ - 好\N{\rENG}- Seven-thirty at the very latest.  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.35,0:07:18.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 嗨  - 你好\N{\rENG}- Hi.  - Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.29,0:07:24.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你还好吗？ - 很好，你呢？\N{\rENG}- How are you?  - Good, and you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.79,0:07:28.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,挺好，是的，我很好，我…\N{\rENG}I'm good, yeah, I'm great. I'm....
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.40,0:07:31.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你愿意…我是说…去喝杯咖啡什么的吗？\N{\rENG}Do you wanna, maybe,get a cup of coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:34.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,他不是说你要赶飞机吗？\N{\rENG}Didn't he just say you have a plane to catch?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.97,0:07:38.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊…不过时间还早\N{\rENG}Yeah. But, I mean, I have a little time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.28,0:07:42.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那好吧  - 好吗？好，那，让我…\N{\rENG}- Okay.  - Yeah? All right, well, let me....
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.78,0:07:44.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在外面等你\N{\rENG}I'll meet you outside. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.62,0:07:48.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,我出去一下，喝杯咖啡\N{\rENG}Excuse me. I'm just gonna go get a cup of coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.22,0:07:51.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我七点一刻回来  - 这些书你都签了名吗？\N{\rENG}- I'll be back at 7:15.  - Did you sign all these?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.62,0:07:54.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是的，我肯定签了  - 拿着你的司机菲利普的名片…\N{\rENG}- Yeah, I sure did.  - Get your driver Philippe's card...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.46,0:07:56.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,…这样你要是晚了，就用手机给他打电话\N{\rENG}...so you can call his cell if you're running late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.19,0:07:59.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们会把你的包放在车里，这样你就不会晚了\N{\rENG}We'll put your bags in the car so you're not late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.96,0:08:02.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好的，谢谢你  - {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}非常感谢\N{\rENG}- All right, thanks for everything.  - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.83,0:08:06.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁是菲利普？\N{\rENG}Which one's Philippe?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.81,0:08:09.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}菲利普，把你的名片给他，上面有你的手机号码\N{\rENG}Philippe, passe lui ta carte pour qu'il forme ta numero portable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.45,0:08:10.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}谢谢\N{\rENG}Merci.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.75,0:08:28.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真难以置信你会在这里  - 我就住在巴黎\N{\rENG}- I can't believe you're here.  - I live here in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.49,0:08:32.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,你真的不用多呆几天吗？你不用再和谁谈什么了吗？\N{\rENG}Are you sure you don't have to stay?You're not supposed to talk more?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.03,0:08:35.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，他们都开始烦我了，我昨晚整夜都在这里\N{\rENG}They're sick of me.I spent the night here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.30,0:08:38.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 哦，真的吗？ - 是啊，他们楼上有间阁楼\N{\rENG}- You did?  - Yeah, they got a loft upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.00,0:08:41.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你怎么样？这感觉真奇怪  - 我很好\N{\rENG}- How are you? This is so weird.  - I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.60,0:08:45.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 见到你真高兴！ - 见到你真高兴！\N{\rENG}- It's good to see you.  - It's good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.68,0:08:50.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那你想去喝杯咖啡吗？ - 哦，当然\N{\rENG}- So you want to go to a cafe?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.31,0:08:52.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,那好，那边不远有一家很不错\N{\rENG}Okay. There's one a little further that I like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.85,0:08:56.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我刚才见到你的时候我都快傻了\N{\rENG}I thought I was gonna totally lose it in there when I first saw you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.95,0:08:58.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,你怎么会知道我会来这的呢？\N{\rENG}How did you know I was gonna be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.89,0:09:03.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是我在巴黎最喜欢的书店了，你可以坐在那里看一天书\N{\rENG}It's my favorite bookstore in Paris.You can sit down for hours and read.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.46,0:09:05.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很喜欢这样，那儿是有跳蚤，不过，你知道的…\N{\rENG}I love it. There's fleas,but, you know....
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.63,0:09:07.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道，我简直感觉昨晚有只猫睡在我头上\N{\rENG}I know. I think a cat slept on my head last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.16,0:09:10.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一个月前就书店日历上看到你的照片\N{\rENG}I saw your picture on the calendar about a month ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.97,0:09:12.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道你会来这里\N{\rENG}...and that you were going to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.27,0:09:16.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,有意思的是，我读了你的书，一小段而已\N{\rENG}It's funny, because I read an article on your book...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.34,0:09:20.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我有种朦朦胧胧的的亲切感  - 朦朦胧胧？是吗？\N{\rENG}- ...and it sounded vaguely familiar.  - Vaguely? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.71,0:09:24.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，只不过是在见到你的照片之后才有的，所以…\N{\rENG}But I didn't put it all together until I saw your photo. So....
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.71,0:09:26.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看过那书了吗？\N{\rENG}Did you have a chance to read it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.08,0:09:28.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，我…\N{\rENG}Yes, I....
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.68,0:09:31.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的书让我感到惊喜，你应该体会得到的\N{\rENG}I was really, really surprised,as you can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.35,0:09:33.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，我对它爱不释手\N{\rENG}I mean, I had to read it twice, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.19,0:09:36.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是吗？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- Yeah?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.45,0:09:37.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}写得马马虎虎？\N{\rENG}Comme ci comme ca?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.66,0:09:40.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，我很喜欢，非常浪漫！\N{\rENG}No, I liked it. It's very romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.43,0:09:43.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,我平时不爱看类似的书，但是你写的真好\N{\rENG}I usually don't like that,but it's really well-written.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.33,0:09:46.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 写的非常好，祝贺你！ - 好吧，谢谢\N{\rENG}- It's well-written. Congratulations.  - All right. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.74,0:09:48.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 等等  - 怎么啦？\N{\rENG}- Wait.  - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.84,0:09:52.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,在我们出发前，我得问你…\N{\rENG}Before we go anywhere,I have to ask you....
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.21,0:09:54.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,没问题，什么事？\N{\rENG}Sure. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.94,0:09:57.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,那年十二月，你去维也纳了吗？\N{\rENG}Did you show up in Vienna that December?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.82,0:10:04.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 呃，你去了吗？ - 没有，我没能去成，但是…你去了吗？\N{\rENG}- Did you?  - No, I couldn't. But did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.35,0:10:07.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我必须要知道，这对我很重要！ - 为什么，既然你都没去？\N{\rENG}- I need to know. It's important to me.  - Why, if you didn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:10.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,那，你去了吗？\N{\rENG}Well, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.26,0:10:11.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.40,0:10:14.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，谢天谢地你没去！\N{\rENG}Thank God you didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.10,0:10:16.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 哦，天啊  - 谢天谢地你没去\N{\rENG}- Oh, my God.  - Thank God you didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.10,0:10:20.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，幸亏我没去，你也没去，要是我们两个只有一个人去了…\N{\rENG}Thank God I didn't and you didn't.If one of us had showed up alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.77,0:10:23.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,- …那简直是糟透了  - 我知道，我知道，我一直担心这个\N{\rENG}- ...that would have sucked.  - I was so concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.37,0:10:27.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一直因为没去而内疚，但是我确实没法！我祖母那之前几天过世了\N{\rENG}I felt horrible about not being there,but I couldn't. My grandma died...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.44,0:10:29.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,那天是她下葬的日子，十二月十六日\N{\rENG}...and she was buried that day,December 16th.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.91,0:10:32.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 她过世了？就是布达佩斯的那一位？ - 是的，你还记得？\N{\rENG}- The one in Budapest?  - Yes. You remember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.72,0:10:35.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 当然，我什么都记得  - 噢，对了，你书中还提到了\N{\rENG}- I remember everything.  - Of course, it was in your book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.65,0:10:38.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,总之，我的确想过去维也纳的\N{\rENG}But anyway, I was about to fly to Vienna, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.15,0:10:43.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是噩耗突然传来，我只能去参加葬礼了\N{\rENG}...and we heard the news about her,and of course I had to go to the funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.39,0:10:45.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，听到这个真让人难过\N{\rENG}Yeah, I'm sorry to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.29,0:10:49.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道，反正你也没去…\N{\rENG}I know. But you weren't there anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.26,0:10:51.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,等等，你为什么没去？\N{\rENG}Wait. Why weren't you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.97,0:10:55.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要是能去的话一定会去的，我定了计划，而且我…\N{\rENG}I would have been there if I could have. I made plans....
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.50,0:10:57.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你最好能找到个好一点的理由！\N{\rENG}You better have a good reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.94,0:10:59.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么了？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.38,0:11:02.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，不！\N{\rENG}Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.48,0:11:05.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,你去那了，是吗？\N{\rENG}No, you were there, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.75,0:11:08.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，不，真糟糕！\N{\rENG}Oh, no, that's terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.62,0:11:10.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道，我笑了，不过我不是有意的！\N{\rENG}I'm laughing, but I don't mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.49,0:11:12.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,你当时生我气了吧，一定是的\N{\rENG}Did you hate me?You must've hated me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:14.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你一直都在生我的气吧？一定是的  - 没有\N{\rENG}- Have you been hating me all this time?You have.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.96,0:11:16.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 有，你生我气了  - 没有\N{\rENG}- Yes, you have.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.49,0:11:18.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,但你现在不生气了，对吧？\N{\rENG}But you can't hate me now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.53,0:11:21.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我是说，我祖母…  - 我没生你的气，又不是什么大事\N{\rENG}- I mean, my grandma...  - I don't hate you. It's no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.90,0:11:24.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我大老远飞过去，你却放我的鸽子\N{\rENG}I flew all the way over there,you blew the thing off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.63,0:11:27.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,于是我的人生自此一蹶不振，不过，这又算什么呢\N{\rENG}My life's been a big nosedive since,but it's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.94,0:11:30.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我只是开玩笑，开玩笑  - 别这么说，我真无法相信\N{\rENG}- No, I'm kidding.  - Don't say that. I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.97,0:11:33.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一定是把你气疯了，我真抱歉\N{\rENG}You must have been so angry with me. I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.61,0:11:36.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真的很想去的，没什么比这个更重要了！\N{\rENG}I really wanted to be there,more than anything in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.31,0:11:39.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不开玩笑了，我发誓…  - 你不能生气啊，我祖母…\N{\rENG}- Honestly, I swear...  - You can't be angry, my grandmother...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.21,0:11:42.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,我懂，我真的想到了，你大概就是被这种事情缠住了\N{\rENG}I know. I honestly thought that something like that might have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.05,0:11:45.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我确实是非常失望，不过…\N{\rENG}I was definitely bummed, but....
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:49.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,我感到最遗憾的还是因为我们没有交换电话号码，或者任何其他个人信息\N{\rENG}Mostly I was mad we hadn't exchanged any phone numbers or any information.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.19,0:11:51.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,瞧瞧我们干的傻事，没法彼此联系\N{\rENG}That was so stupid.No way to get in touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.36,0:11:53.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 对啊，没法继续下去了  - 我甚至不知道你姓什么\N{\rENG}- Nothing to go on.  - I didn't know your last name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.86,0:11:57.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,记得吗，我们都担心如果我们开始通信，打电话…\N{\rENG}Remember, we were both afraid if we started writing and calling...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.23,0:12:00.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,- …感觉会不会慢慢的就变淡了  - 是啊，而且肯定不会慢慢变淡\N{\rENG}- ...that it would slowly fade out.  - lt definitely wasn't a slow fade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.97,0:12:02.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,肯定不会\N{\rENG}No, it sure wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.37,0:12:04.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们都怀念曾经拥有的感觉\N{\rENG}We wanted to pick up where we left off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.37,0:12:07.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果这份感觉可以永存的话，那就再好不过了\N{\rENG}Which would have been fine if it had worked. Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.08,0:12:10.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,那么…\N{\rENG}So....
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.21,0:12:14.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你在维也纳待了多久？ - 就几天\N{\rENG}- How long were you in Vienna, then?  - Just a couple days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.28,0:12:18.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,你碰到其他女孩了吗？\N{\rENG}Did you meet another girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.35,0:12:20.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,啊，是啊，她叫格蕾岑，她棒极了\N{\rENG}Yeah, her name was Gretchen and she was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.56,0:12:22.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真的？ - 是啊，事实上，那书是写你们两个的\N{\rENG}- You did?  - The book's really a composite of the two of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.65,0:12:27.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真的吗？ - 没这回事，我只是开玩笑！你不会相信的，我甚至还回到火车站过\N{\rENG}- Really?  - No, I'm kidding. You wouldn't believe... I even went back to the train station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.06,0:12:32.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我支了个牌子，写了我旅馆的电话号码，以免你来晚了找不到\N{\rENG}I put up signs of my number in the hotel in case you'd been delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.33,0:12:35.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我真是个笨蛋  - 我们这边走，有人打电话给你吗？\N{\rENG}- I was a total dork.  - Let's go this way. Did you get any calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.40,0:12:38.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,有几个妓女，拉皮条的\N{\rENG}Just a couple hookers looking for a gig.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.61,0:12:41.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，那真是糟，我是说，你指望让我说什么呢\N{\rENG}No, it was awful, I mean,what do you want me to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.34,0:12:42.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，太让人伤心了，我真抱歉！\N{\rENG}It's so sad. I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.98,0:12:46.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就那么转悠了几天，最后，就飞回去了\N{\rENG}I walked around for a couple days.Eventually, I flew home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.25,0:12:48.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,还欠了我爸两千块\N{\rENG}I owed my dad 2000 bucks...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.72,0:12:50.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,他可是警告我不要碰法国鸡\N{\rENG}...who had warned me about French chicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.92,0:12:52.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,他怎么对你形容法国女人的？\N{\rENG}What did he tell you about French women?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.02,0:12:55.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,没什么，他，他从来没有遇见过法国女人\N{\rENG}Nothing. He's never met any French women.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.29,0:12:57.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,他从来没有去过比密西西比河更东的地方\N{\rENG}He's never been east of the Mississippi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.73,0:13:01.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,那你干嘛不加上一句，“六个月过去了，那个法国婊子还是没出现”\N{\rENG}Why didn't you put, "Six months later,the French bitch didn't show up"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.13,0:13:03.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，可是我差点这么做了\N{\rENG}No, but I did, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.93,0:13:06.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你真的想过？ - 是的，我是说，我让它看起来更有悬念\N{\rENG}- You did?  - Yeah. No. I made it more hopeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.07,0:13:09.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,我写了一段虚构的情节，说你最后出现了\N{\rENG}I wrote this fictional version where you do show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.81,0:13:12.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 哦，你怎么写的？ - 呃…\N{\rENG}- Oh, what happens?  - Well....
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.58,0:13:15.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么了？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.61,0:13:18.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,呃，我们整整做了十天爱，这还没完\N{\rENG}We make love for about 10 days straight,that's one part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.78,0:13:21.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 哦，真有意思，一个法国荡妇…  - 没错\N{\rENG}- Interesting. So the French slut, right?  - Yeah, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.78,0:13:24.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,从那以后，他们开始了解对方\N{\rENG}It's just then they get to know each other better...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.45,0:13:26.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后他们意识到彼此并不合适\N{\rENG}...and realize they don't get along at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:29.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我喜欢这样，看起来更真实  - 我的编辑可不这么想\N{\rENG}- I like that. It's more real.  - My editor didn't think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.13,0:13:32.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁都想相信爱情，为了畅销嘛，对吧？\N{\rENG}Everyone wants to believe in love.It sells.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.43,0:13:34.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，就是如此，所以…\N{\rENG}Yeah, exactly, so....
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.13,0:13:37.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是说你一切都好，对吧？\N{\rENG}So things are going well for you,right? I mean....
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.93,0:13:41.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我是说，你的书是美国畅销书…  - 只是本小小的畅销书\N{\rENG}- Your book is a bestseller in the U.S.  - It's a tiny bestseller.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:43.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 哦，别谦虚啦…  - 好吧，没错，理论上说，是的\N{\rENG}- Oh, come on.  - All right. Officially, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.57,0:13:46.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,可大多数人连莫比·迪克的书都没读过，又怎么会来读我的？\N{\rENG}Most people haven't read Moby Dick.Why should they read my book?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:49.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也没读过莫比·迪克的书，可是我就喜欢你的书，所以…\N{\rENG}I haven't read Moby Dick and I liked your book.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.28,0:13:51.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢  - 即使…\N{\rENG}- Thanks.  - Even though...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.78,0:13:54.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得你把那一晚描绘得太完美了\N{\rENG}...I thought you idealized the night of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.75,0:13:56.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,嘿，我说，这可是小说\N{\rENG}Come on, it's officially a fiction, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.62,0:13:58.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我本来就得…  - 我知道，我知道\N{\rENG}- I'm supposed to...  - I know, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.49,0:14:01.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道，有些时候，你让我看起来…\N{\rENG}I know. I thought there were times where you made me....
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.92,0:14:06.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,呃，我是说她，不，还是我…算啦，管她是谁\N{\rENG}Well, I mean, her, right?No, me. Okay, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.46,0:14:09.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 总之有点神经质！ - 你确实有点啊，不是吗？\N{\rENG}- A little bit neurotic.  - You are a bit like that, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.77,0:14:13.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你认为我神经质？ - 没有，这是个玩笑而已！\N{\rENG}- You think I'm neurotic?  - No, no, no. Come on, I'm kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.17,0:14:15.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,我哪那么写了，我才没有呢\N{\rENG}Where did I do that? I didn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:17.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,我这人就是这样的，你知道的…\N{\rENG}Oh, maybe it's just me, you know....
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.11,0:14:21.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,读到一个故事，知道故事是根据自己来写的\N{\rENG}Reading something, knowing the character is storied based on you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.34,0:14:24.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,这既让人受宠若惊，也让人心神不宁\N{\rENG}...it's both flattering and disturbing at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.21,0:14:25.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么会让人心神不宁的？\N{\rENG}How is it disturbing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.95,0:14:30.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道，只是…成为他人记忆中的一部分\N{\rENG}I don't know. Just being part of someone else's memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.32,0:14:32.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,透过你的眼看到我自己\N{\rENG}Seeing myself through your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.12,0:14:35.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,你写了多久？\N{\rENG}How long did it take you to write it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.49,0:14:38.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,呃，三四年吧，时断时续的\N{\rENG}Three or four years, on and off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.49,0:14:41.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,哇，你花了那么长时间就为了写一个晚上发生的事情？\N{\rENG}Wow, that's a really long time to be writing about one night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.86,0:14:44.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，我知道，你说的没错\N{\rENG}Yeah, I know. Tell you about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.83,0:14:47.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,我总是认为你已经忘记我了\N{\rENG}I always assumed you had forgotten me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.70,0:14:50.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有，我心目中你的印象非常清晰\N{\rENG}No, I had a pretty clear picture of you in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.67,0:14:53.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我得告诉你件事情，我…  - 怎么了？\N{\rENG}- I have to tell you something. I just....  - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.38,0:14:55.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,这么久以来，我一直想和你聊天，你知道吗，而现在…\N{\rENG}I've wanted to talk to you for so long that now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.62,0:14:56.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是啊，我也是  - 现在梦想成真了\N{\rENG}- Me,too.  - It's just surreal, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.62,0:14:58.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我却觉得不知道该说什么了\N{\rENG}I feel like everything should be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.18,0:15:01.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,我懂，我懂，我们还有多长时间？二十分钟又三十秒？\N{\rENG}How long do we have?Twenty minutes and 30 seconds?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.82,0:15:04.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，我们有的是时间，我想多和你聊聊\N{\rENG}We got more than that.I wanna know about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.32,0:15:06.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,告诉我你在做什么？\N{\rENG}Tell me, what are you doing?What are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.16,0:15:11.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,呃，从哪开始呢…我为绿十字会工作，那是个环保组织\N{\rENG}Where to start? I work for Green Cross.It's an environmental organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.99,0:15:13.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们是干嘛的？\N{\rENG}What are they all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.53,0:15:16.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个嘛，基本上来说，我们会关注一些环境问题\N{\rENG}We basically work on different environment issues...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.26,0:15:18.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,比如净化水质，或者销毁化学武器什么的\N{\rENG}...from clean water to disarmament of chemical weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.07,0:15:21.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗，涉及环境的国际法什么的\N{\rENG}International laws that deal with the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.70,0:15:24.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那，你为他们做什么？ - 我们走这边\N{\rENG}- What do you do for them?  - We're going this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.51,0:15:25.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,很多事了\N{\rENG}Different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.04,0:15:29.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,比如去年，我在印度待了一阵，在一间水处理工厂工作\N{\rENG}Like, last year I was in lndia for quite a while,working on a water-treatment plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.71,0:15:34.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,那里的棉纺工业是主要的污染源，所以…\N{\rENG}Well, the cotton industry there is a major source of pollution, so....
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.22,0:15:37.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，听起来你的确做了一些有意义的事情\N{\rENG}I mean, it sounds like you're actually doing something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.35,0:15:40.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,大多数人，也包括我，只是…你知道吗，无所事事\N{\rENG}Most people, myself included,just sit around and bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.96,0:15:45.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,美国消耗了世界上大多数资源，箱式轿车尤其如此\N{\rENG}You know, how America's consuming all the world's resources, SUVs suck...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.79,0:15:47.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,全球也在变暖…\N{\rENG}...global warming is real...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.40,0:15:50.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,很高兴你不是那种狂妄自大的美国人\N{\rENG}I'm relieved to hear you're not one of those "freedom fries" Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.93,0:15:53.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过，你是怎么会去做这个的呢？\N{\rENG}Hey, you know...But how'd you get into that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.54,0:15:56.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,啊，我政治系毕了业，那时我希望为政府工作\N{\rENG}I came out of political science,hoping to work for the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.04,0:15:59.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 而我确实也替他们干了一阵，哎，太糟了！ - 不好吗？\N{\rENG}- And I did for a little while. Terrible.  - Not good?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.94,0:16:03.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，不好，我们这边走，总之，我烦透了…\N{\rENG}Yeah, no. anyway, I got really tired... Let's go this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.78,0:16:06.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,…与朋友无休止的讨论…\N{\rENG}Having this endless conversation with friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.25,0:16:08.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,关于世界怎么会分裂成这样的问题\N{\rENG}...about how the world was falling to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.72,0:16:11.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我意识到我真正想要做的\N{\rENG}So I decided what I really wanted to do was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.32,0:16:14.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是找到一些可以做好的事情，然后努力做好它们\N{\rENG}...to find things that could be fixed and try to fix them, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.89,0:16:18.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一直觉得你会做这种超酷的事情的\N{\rENG}You know, I always thought you'd be doing something cool like that. I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.83,0:16:23.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢！不过我真的很幸运，能找到份自己喜欢的工作\N{\rENG}Thanks. I just feel really, really lucky to be doing a job I like, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.97,0:16:25.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.60,0:16:30.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗，事实上我曾经非常彷徨，一会儿认为这个世界已经没救了…\N{\rENG}I actually alternate in between thinking everything is irrevocably screwed up...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.51,0:16:32.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,一会儿又认为很多时候还是有转机的\N{\rENG}...and things might be getting better in ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:35.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,转机？为什么要这么悲观呢？\N{\rENG}Better? How could you possibly say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.61,0:16:37.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个嘛，我只是说，你明白吗，比如…\N{\rENG}Well, I just mean, you know, like....
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.58,0:16:41.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道这听起来很奇怪，不过有些事情还是要从好的方面来看\N{\rENG}I know it sounds weird, but there are things to be optimistic about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.45,0:16:46.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啦，我知道你的书畅销，这非常好，我为你感到高兴，不过…\N{\rENG}Okay.... I know your book is selling,which is great, I'm very happy for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.35,0:16:49.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我告诉你真实的世界，好吗？世界现在是一团糟！\N{\rENG}But let me break the news to you:The world is a mess right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:52.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,从西方世界的观点来看来说，世界的确在变好\N{\rENG}From a Western view,things are getting a bit better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.53,0:16:56.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们正把工业重心转移到发展中国家，那里我们能获得便宜的劳动力…\N{\rENG}We're moving industry to developing nations where we can get cheap labor...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.33,0:16:59.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而不去管任何环保法律，军火工业蓬勃发展\N{\rENG}...free of any environmental laws.The weapon industry is booming.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.77,0:17:02.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,每年有五百万人因为水质污染而死去，而这些本来是可以避免的\N{\rENG}Five million people die a year from preventable water disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.94,0:17:05.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,告诉我，这样的世界还不够糟糕吗？我没有生气，我没有生气\N{\rENG}How is the world getting better?I'm not angry, I'm not angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.14,0:17:08.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过，说吧，我想知道，我很有兴趣！\N{\rENG}But come on, I want to know.I'm interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:11.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，我知道世界上有很多严重的问题\N{\rENG}I realize that there are a lot of serious problems in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.15,0:17:14.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 太好了，谢谢你！ - 我的意思是说\N{\rENG}- Okay. Thank you.  - I mean, I don't even have...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.62,0:17:17.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我在亚洲根本找不到出版商出我的书  - 好啦\N{\rENG}- ...one publisher in the Asian market.  - Okay. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.65,0:17:21.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 说“住嘴”！ - 怎么啦？住嘴\N{\rENG}- Say stop.  - What? Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.79,0:17:25.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,听我说，我想说的只是更多的人意识到这一点了，人们正在反击！\N{\rENG}Look, all I'm saying is there's more awareness. People are gonna fight back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.86,0:17:28.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,世界还是有可能变得更好的，因为更多像你这样的人…\N{\rENG}The world might be getting better because people like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.03,0:17:30.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,…学会了说出自己的想法\N{\rENG}...are educated and speaking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.13,0:17:34.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,最起码的，那些环保问题\N{\rENG}Even the very notion of conservation,environmental issues...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.67,0:17:37.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,最近才出现在词典里\N{\rENG}...weren't in the vocabulary till fairly recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.21,0:17:41.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,而现在他们已经成了规范了，而最后他们都可能被实现\N{\rENG}And they're becoming the norm and eventually might be what's expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.51,0:17:44.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我同意你的看法，但是同时，这也很危险！\N{\rENG}I agree with what you're saying,but at the same time it's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.68,0:17:47.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,帝国主义国家会用你这种观点…\N{\rENG}An imperialist country can use that kind of thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.48,0:17:49.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,…来为他们经济上的巧取豪夺找到依据\N{\rENG}...to justify their economic greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.09,0:17:55.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是在针对某一个帝国主义国家吧，法国佬？\N{\rENG}Is there any particular imperialist country you have in mind, there, Frenchie?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.32,0:17:57.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没，没有  - 没有吗？\N{\rENG}- No, not really.  - No?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.52,0:17:59.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}晚上好  - {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}晚上好\N{\rENG}- Bonsoir!  - Bonsoir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.93,0:18:06.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你愿意坐那边吗？ - 当然，这真不错\N{\rENG}- So you wanna sit over there?  - Yeah, this is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.84,0:18:09.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，哇，可能我想说的只是…\N{\rENG}Oh, wow. Maybe what I'm saying is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.81,0:18:12.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,…世界的命运就像一个人的命运一样\N{\rENG}...the world might be evolving the way a person evolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.87,0:18:15.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，比如我，我在退步了吗？\N{\rENG}Like, I mean, me, for example.Am I getting worse?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.08,0:18:20.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在进步吗？我也不知道！当我更年轻的时候，我也更健康…\N{\rENG}Am I improving? I don't know.When I was younger, I was healthier...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.45,0:18:22.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,…但是我充满了危机感，你懂吗？\N{\rENG}...but I was wracked with insecurity,you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:25.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在，我变老了，遇到的问题也更复杂了\N{\rENG}Now I'm older and my problems are deeper...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.85,0:18:27.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我也更知道怎么来处理它们了\N{\rENG}...but I'm more equipped to handle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.46,0:18:30.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,那么，你碰到什么问题了？\N{\rENG}So, what are your problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.19,0:18:36.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在？没事，我没事，我只是…\N{\rENG}Right now I don't have any.I don't, you know? I'm just...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.87,0:18:38.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,…我真他妈高兴能在这！\N{\rENG}...damn happy to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:40.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也一样\N{\rENG}Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.61,0:18:45.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,那，你在巴黎待了多久了？\N{\rENG}So how long have you been in Paris?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.07,0:18:49.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我昨晚才来，十二天之内我跑了十个城市\N{\rENG}I got in last night.I've done 10 cities in 12 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.71,0:18:52.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,我累极了，所以我很高兴一切都结束了\N{\rENG}I'm wrecked. I'm so glad it's over,you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.25,0:18:53.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,我已经厌倦了这种推销\N{\rENG}I'm tired of being a huckster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.28,0:18:55.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 嗨  - 你好\N{\rENG}- Hi.  - Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.17,0:18:55.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}请问您想要点什么？\N{\rENG}Qu'est que je vous sers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.98,0:18:57.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,你要点什么？\N{\rENG}What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.72,0:18:58.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,一杯咖啡…\N{\rENG}A cup of coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:03.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}请给我来一杯咖啡和一片柠檬\N{\rENG}Un cafe et un citron presse,s'il vous plait.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.46,0:19:07.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,天，我爱死这家咖啡馆了，我真希望美国也有这样的地方\N{\rENG}God, I love this cafe. I wish they had places like this in the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.60,0:19:10.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，当我住那边的时候，我可想念咖啡馆了\N{\rENG}Yeah, I missed cafes when I was living over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.30,0:19:13.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，我是找到了一些我喜欢的地方，但是那…\N{\rENG}I mean, I find a few places I really liked, but there was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.40,0:19:17.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你…你在美国呆过？ - 是的，从…九六年到九九年\N{\rENG}- You were living in the U.S.?  - Yes, from '96 to '99.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.61,0:19:19.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我那时在纽约州立大学上学\N{\rENG}I was studying at NYU.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.57,0:19:22.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，天啊，真难以相信，塞琳！\N{\rENG}Oh, God, don't tell me that, Celine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.41,0:19:24.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 怎么了？ - 没什么，只是…\N{\rENG}- What?  - No, it's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.65,0:19:26.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没什么，我是说我…  - 怎么了\N{\rENG}- Nothing, I mean, I...  - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.51,0:19:29.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我从九八年起就住在纽约了，你懂吗，我们那时都在那里！\N{\rENG}I've been living in New York since '98.We were there at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.09,0:19:31.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 纽约？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- In New York?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.82,0:19:36.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,奇怪的是，事实上有几次我想到过可能会遇见你，\N{\rENG}That's weird. It actually crossed my mind a few times that I might run into you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.69,0:19:39.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,…但是几率太低了，对吧？而且…\N{\rENG}...but the odds are so slim, right? So....
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.63,0:19:41.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,我那时都不知道你住哪个城市\N{\rENG}I didn't even know what city you were in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.70,0:19:45.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你不是住德克萨斯吗？ - 是的，没错，正是如此，我只是…\N{\rENG}- Weren't you somewhere in Texas?  - Yeah, yeah, definitely. I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.43,0:19:48.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在那住了很久，我只是…你明白吗，到纽约换换环境\N{\rENG}I was for a long time. I just,you know, wanted to try New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.97,0:19:52.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,那你为什么回来了呢？\N{\rENG}What brought you back here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.84,0:19:54.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,一是我读完了硕士\N{\rENG}I had finished my master's, for one...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.04,0:19:57.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,再来，我的签证到期了\N{\rENG}...and no visa, no more visa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.48,0:20:01.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,而且，不算这些，我也开始有点妄想狂了，媒体上那么多的暴力事件\N{\rENG}And I was starting to get paranoid.All the violence in the medias:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.02,0:20:05.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,黑帮啦，谋杀啦…尤其是那连环杀手\N{\rENG}Gang violence, murders,especially serial killers....
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.92,0:20:08.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,而最后决定性的原因是…\N{\rENG}But the final straw was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:11.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,…有天晚上我听到外面消防通道上有些动静\N{\rENG}...one night I heard some noise on my fire escape...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.86,0:20:14.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,于是我打了九一一，最后警察终于来了\N{\rENG}...so I called 911,and the cops came eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.63,0:20:18.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 大概三小时以后吧  - 是啊，那时候我已经被先奸后杀了\N{\rENG}- Like three hours later.  - Yeah, after I had been raped and killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.73,0:20:21.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有啦，来的只是一个男一女两个警察\N{\rENG}No, but it was a man and a woman officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.47,0:20:23.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,当那个女警到楼下挪警车的时候\N{\rENG}I was explaining what I had heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.67,0:20:25.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,我向他解释我听到的声音\N{\rENG}...when the woman had to go move the police car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.14,0:20:27.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,那时只有那个男警察和我一起\N{\rENG}I was left alone with the male cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.01,0:20:32.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,而他立刻问我是不是有枪…我说没有，我当然没有了\N{\rENG}Right away he asked me if I had a gun,and I said, "No, of course not."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.68,0:20:35.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后他对我说：“是吗，你最好考虑去买一把”\N{\rENG}And he told me, "Well, you better think about getting one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.75,0:20:39.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,“这里是美国，不是法国”\N{\rENG}This is america, not France. Okay? "
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.25,0:20:42.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后我对他说，我完全不懂怎么开枪\N{\rENG}And I said to him, "l have no idea how to shoot a gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.59,0:20:45.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,而且，我对枪支也没有兴趣\N{\rENG}...and I have no interest in firearms whatsoever."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.33,0:20:49.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,于是他抽出他的枪，就像这样，然后他说：\N{\rENG}And that's when he pulled out his gun,like this, and he went:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.33,0:20:54.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,“总有一天，你会碰到这么个东西指着你的脸”\N{\rENG}"Well, one day, you're gonna have something like this in your face...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.04,0:20:57.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,“如果你想活的长久点”\N{\rENG}...and if you wanna have a long life...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.97,0:21:01.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,“你就必须决定是不是要干掉他们”\N{\rENG}...you're gonna have to choose between you or them."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.84,0:21:07.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后他们就走了，而第二天早上，我就打电话申请持有枪支\N{\rENG}And then they left. And the next morning I called for an application to get a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.42,0:21:09.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我拿把枪！我是说，那可真可怕…\N{\rENG}Me with a gun.I mean, that's really scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.12,0:21:12.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是然后我意识到有些事不对劲\N{\rENG}But then I realized something was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.49,0:21:16.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,那警察拔枪的举动，还有其他的事…\N{\rENG}The way that cop had pulled his gun out,and everything, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.22,0:21:18.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,于是我取消了对枪的预订\N{\rENG}So I canceled my demand for the gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.23,0:21:21.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后我打电话给警察局，想要对那个警察的行为进行申诉，但是…\N{\rENG}...and I called the police and tried to complain about that cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.53,0:21:24.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 发生什么事了？ - 要填太多表了\N{\rENG}- What happened with that?  - It was so much paperwork...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.27,0:21:27.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后我就怕了，就凭我这种学生签证…\N{\rENG}...and then I got scared,with my shitty student visa...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.27,0:21:29.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你认为你会被遣送出境  - 没错！于是我放弃了…\N{\rENG}- Thought you'd get deported?  - Exactly. I gave up...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.87,0:21:31.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后就忘记了整件事\N{\rENG}...and forgot about the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.87,0:21:35.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 其实，我想我永远也不会忘记的  - 当然了\N{\rENG}- Well, I guess I never forgot.  - Obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.64,0:21:38.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是，我真的还是喜欢在那里的日子\N{\rENG}But still, you know,I really enjoyed being there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.41,0:21:41.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我怀念美国的很多事  - 是吗，比如？\N{\rENG}- There's lots of things I miss in the U.S.  - Yeah? Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.52,0:21:45.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯…\N{\rENG}Well....
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.29,0:21:47.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,那里的人们通常都有好心情\N{\rENG}The overall good mood people have there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.02,0:21:50.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,比如，你知道的，即使有的时候胡乱问候\N{\rENG}Like, even if it can be bullshit sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.26,0:21:53.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,比如“你好吗？”“很好！”“你好吗？”“很好！”\N{\rENG}Like, "How you doing? " "Great." "How you doing? " "Great!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.46,0:21:55.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,“祝你今天愉快！”\N{\rENG}"Have a great day!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.03,0:21:59.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也不知道，巴黎人的脾气可不好，你发现了吗？\N{\rENG}I don't know. Parisians can be so grumpy. Have you noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.83,0:22:02.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有啊，每个人在我看来都很高兴啊\N{\rENG}No, everybody seems pretty happy to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.17,0:22:06.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 他们总是不高兴…  - 他们总是不高兴？\N{\rENG}- They're not happy. No.  - They're not happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.27,0:22:09.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是，他们也高兴，我不知道，我说的只是法国男人，他们快把我逼疯了！\N{\rENG}No, they are. I don't know. I just mean French men. They drive me nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.84,0:22:11.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么回事？他们怎么了？\N{\rENG}What is it? What about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.58,0:22:14.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯，他们很好，不深入接触的话非常好\N{\rENG}Well, they're very nice.They're great, you know, to be around.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.78,0:22:16.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们喜欢食物，酒，他们做东西很好吃…\N{\rENG}They love food, wine,they're great cooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.95,0:22:18.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是，不知道，可能我只是运气不好\N{\rENG}But I've had really bad luck with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.12,0:22:20.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么这么说？什么意思？\N{\rENG}Why? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.59,0:22:24.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我想他们不是那么…  - 怎么？\N{\rENG}- Well, I guess they're not as...  - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.79,0:22:26.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么说呢\N{\rENG}What's the word?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.43,0:22:30.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好色？他们不那么好色…  - 好色？\N{\rENG}- Horny? They're not as horny.  - Horny?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.93,0:22:35.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,等等，听我这么说怎样，对此，我以身为美国人而骄傲\N{\rENG}Wait, listen to me on this one. In that regard, I am proud to be an american.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.37,0:22:36.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,你确实应该如此，仅对此一点\N{\rENG}And you should be.In that regard only.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.65,0:22:38.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}谢谢\N{\rENG}Merci.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.47,0:22:40.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,你去过东欧吗？\N{\rENG}Have you ever spent time in Eastern Europe?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.94,0:22:43.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,东欧？没，没有…谢谢\N{\rENG}Eastern... No, I don't.Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.48,0:22:47.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得当我十多岁的时候我去过华沙\N{\rENG}I remember as a teenager I went to Warsaw...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.22,0:22:49.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,那时它还是共产主义的那一套\N{\rENG}...when it was still a strict communist regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.98,0:22:52.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 对此我是一点也不支持  - 当然…\N{\rENG}- Which I don't approve of at all.  - Sure you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.59,0:22:54.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不是，我才没有…  - 好啦，我只是开玩笑！\N{\rENG}- No, I don't.  - I'm just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.72,0:22:57.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是，不管怎样，我发现待在那里是件很有意思的事\N{\rENG}But anyway, something about being there was very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.83,0:23:01.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,仅仅几个星期之后，我就有了改变\N{\rENG}After a couple of weeks,something changed in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.23,0:23:04.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,那座城市又阴郁又灰暗…\N{\rENG}The city was quite gloomy and gray...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.60,0:23:07.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是过了一阵以后，我头脑变的更清醒了\N{\rENG}...but after a while,my brain seemed clearer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.50,0:23:09.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在日记上记录了更多的东西\N{\rENG}I was writing more in my journal...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.37,0:23:12.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 很多我以前从来没有过的想法  - 共产主义的想法？\N{\rENG}- ...ideas I'd never thought of before...  - Communist ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.74,0:23:14.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 听着，我可不是…  - 对不起，我…\N{\rENG}- Listen, I'm not...  - I'm sorry, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.14,0:23:16.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好吧  - 继续！\N{\rENG}- Okay.  - Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.11,0:23:19.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,以后我要送你去俄国古拉格集中营\N{\rENG}Okay. I'll send you to a gulag later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.85,0:23:23.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,只是，那花了我好一阵时间，才搞清楚为什么那里让人感觉那么不同\N{\rENG}No. But it took me a while to figure out why I felt so different.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.49,0:23:26.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后有一天，当我穿过一个犹太墓地的时候\N{\rENG}One day, as I was walking through the Jewish cemetery...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.32,0:23:28.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没想通为什么，但是我真的有所改变\N{\rENG}...I don't know why,but it occurred to me there...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.39,0:23:32.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,我意识到过去的两个星期中，我改掉了以前的大多数习惯\N{\rENG}...I realized that I had spent the last two weeks away from most of my habits.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.43,0:23:34.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,电视里说的是我听不懂的语言\N{\rENG}TV was in a language I didn't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.63,0:23:37.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,没什么好买的，也没什么广告\N{\rENG}...there was nothing to buy,no advertisements anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.53,0:23:39.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以，我能做的只有…\N{\rENG}...so all I'd been doing was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.33,0:23:44.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,到处逛，思考，然后写下来，我的大脑好像在休息\N{\rENG}...walk around, think, and write.My brain felt like it was at rest...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.27,0:23:47.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有了那种强烈的情绪，就好像是自然的高潮一样\N{\rENG}...free from the consuming frenzy.It was almost like a natural high.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.08,0:23:52.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,我感觉内心格外平和，没有什么奇怪的冲动要去什么地方\N{\rENG}I felt so peaceful inside.No strange urge to be somewhere else...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.85,0:23:54.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,购物什么的\N{\rENG}...to shop....
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.38,0:23:56.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,一开始这样可能看起来很无聊\N{\rENG}It could have seemed like boredom at first...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.68,0:23:58.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是很快这就让人感到内心非常非常的充实\N{\rENG}...but it became very, very soulful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.45,0:24:01.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,非常有意思，你知道吗？\N{\rENG}It was interesting, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.19,0:24:04.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,你能相信我们上一次漫步在维也纳是九年前的事吗？\N{\rENG}Can you believe it was nine years ago we were walking around Vienna?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.03,0:24:08.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 九年？真难以想象  - 对我来说就好像是两个月之前的事\N{\rENG}- Nine years? No, that's impossible.  - No, it was. It feels like two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.93,0:24:10.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是那是九四年夏天了\N{\rENG}But it was summer '94.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.07,0:24:15.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,我看起来有什么不同吗？\N{\rENG}Do I look any different?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.94,0:24:18.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,有？\N{\rENG}I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.44,0:24:20.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我得看你一丝不挂的样子才知道\N{\rENG}I'd have to see you naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.08,0:24:23.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么？ - 对不起…\N{\rENG}- What?  - I know, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.24,0:24:25.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的发型变了，那时…\N{\rENG}Your hair was different back then.It was like...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.78,0:24:28.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么，一样的啊…  - 把头发放下来，让我看看！\N{\rENG}- It's the same... Oh, down.  - Yeah, take it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.38,0:24:30.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,放下来，好吧，放下来了\N{\rENG}Down. Okay, it was down. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.32,0:24:32.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,好了\N{\rENG}Well? Voila.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.75,0:24:34.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么样？\N{\rENG}So?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.29,0:24:38.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,快点，告诉我\N{\rENG}Okay, come on. Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.76,0:24:44.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,瘦了，我觉得，苗条了\N{\rENG}Skinnier, I think. A little thinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.40,0:24:46.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,你觉得我以前很胖？\N{\rENG}Did you think I was fat before?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.14,0:24:50.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不是  - 你肯定觉得我那时很胖\N{\rENG}- No....  - Yeah, you thought I was a fatty.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.27,0:24:54.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错，你觉得我很胖，你的书写的是个法国胖妞！\N{\rENG}No, you thought I was a fatty. You wrote a book about a fat French girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.48,0:24:56.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 哦，不要！ - 好啦，说真的\N{\rENG}- No, listen.  - Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.61,0:24:58.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看起来漂亮极了！\N{\rENG}Seriously, all right? You look beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.95,0:25:00.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,那你觉得我有什么变化吗？\N{\rENG}Do I look any different?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.28,0:25:04.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有什么…哦，事实上你这多了道皱纹\N{\rENG}No. Not at all.Actually, you have this line.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.02,0:25:07.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我知道  - 看起来好像疤\N{\rENG}- I know.  - It's like a scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.66,0:25:12.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 疤？看起来像被枪打得吧？ - 没有，没有，我挺喜欢的，对不起啦\N{\rENG}- A scar? Like a gunshot wound?  - No, no, no. I like it. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.43,0:25:18.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,有天我做了个有趣的…呃，不，恐怖的梦\N{\rENG}I had this funny... Well, horrible dream the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.27,0:25:23.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我做恶梦，梦见我有三十二岁了\N{\rENG}I was having this awful nightmare that I was 32.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.47,0:25:26.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后当我醒来的时候，我才只有二十三！我就放心了…\N{\rENG}And then I woke up,and I was 23. So relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.87,0:25:29.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是后来我真的从梦里醒来，发现我确实三十二了\N{\rENG}And then I woke up for real,and I was 32.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.68,0:25:32.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好可怕！ - 是会有这种事的\N{\rENG}- Shit, man. It happens.  - Scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.35,0:25:35.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,时间越走越快，看上去，是因为…\N{\rENG}Time goes faster and faster.Apparently, it's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.18,0:25:38.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,从二十岁以后我们身体里的神经键就不再更新了，于是，从那以后我们就开始走下坡路了\N{\rENG}...we don't renew synapses after our 20s, so it's downhill from then on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.82,0:25:42.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜欢变老，你懂吗，会感觉生活更…\N{\rENG}I like getting older, you know?Life feels....
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.12,0:25:46.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道，好像感觉更直接，好像我能欣赏更多东西了\N{\rENG}I don't know, it feels more immediate. Like I can appreciate things more.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.53,0:25:50.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,其实我也一样，我很喜欢\N{\rENG}No, me too, actually. I really love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.57,0:25:52.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我曾经是…\N{\rENG}I was once...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.57,0:25:53.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个乐队里的鼓手\N{\rENG}...a drummer in a band.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.17,0:25:56.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真的？ - 是啊，我们当时真的很棒\N{\rENG}- You were?  - Yeah. We were pretty good, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.97,0:26:01.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过那个主唱，他整天就想着让我们能出唱片\N{\rENG}But the lead-singer guy, he was just so obsessed with us getting a record deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.34,0:26:04.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们整天谈的，想的，就是参加更大的演出\N{\rENG}It's all we talked about, thought about,getting bigger shows.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.51,0:26:08.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,每时每刻都是为了将来的发展，而现在…\N{\rENG}Everything was just focused on the future all the time. And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.18,0:26:10.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,…乐队却已经不存在了\N{\rENG}...the band doesn't even exist anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.22,0:26:12.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在回顾那些我们参加了的表演\N{\rENG}And looking back at the shows we did play...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.79,0:26:15.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,甚至哪怕只是排练，都觉得那么有意思！\N{\rENG}...even rehearsing, it was just so much fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.86,0:26:20.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在我终于能享受那每一分钟了，我能抽一口吗？\N{\rENG}I just... Now I'd enjoy every minute of it.Could I have a drag of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.33,0:26:23.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的书出版了，这事不算小了\N{\rENG}Well, your book has been published.That's a pretty big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.56,0:26:26.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,而且你巡回了整个欧洲来卖它，你觉得能享受其中的每一分钟吗？\N{\rENG}You've been all around Europe.Are you enjoying every minute of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.54,0:26:29.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不太行…  - 不太行？\N{\rENG}- Not really.  - Not really?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.60,0:26:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,不行\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.54,0:26:34.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你还有烟吗？ - 当然有\N{\rENG}- Do you have another one of those?  - Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.31,0:26:37.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,给你\N{\rENG}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.71,0:26:41.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,在我这行里，我见到很多人…哦，对不起…\N{\rENG}In my field, I see these people that... Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.05,0:26:44.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,过于理想，好高骛远\N{\rENG}Come into it with big,idealist visions...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.75,0:26:47.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,想要成为新的领袖，来创建更美好的世界\N{\rENG}...of becoming the new leader that will create a better world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.69,0:26:49.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们乐于见到目标被实现，却对过程没兴趣！\N{\rENG}They enjoy the goal,but not the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.09,0:26:51.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是  - 但事实上…\N{\rENG}- Right.  - But the reality of it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.13,0:26:55.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,真正能改善世界的工作，是日复一日的点滴进步\N{\rENG}...the true work of improving things is in the little achievements.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.76,0:26:58.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这才是应该享受的事  - 你具体指什么呢？\N{\rENG}- That's what you need to enjoy.  - What do you mean, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.93,0:27:02.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,比如，我为一个组织工作，这个组织在墨西哥帮助那里的村民\N{\rENG}I was working for this organization that helped villages in Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.20,0:27:05.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们关心的是怎么把铅笔\N{\rENG}And their concerns was how to get the pencils...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.87,0:27:08.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,送到那些乡村小学的孩子手中\N{\rENG}...sent to the kid in those little country schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.44,0:27:12.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,那不是什么重大的革命性的想法，仅仅是铅笔而已！\N{\rENG}It was not about big,revolutionary ideas. It was about pencils.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.65,0:27:16.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,我见到过那些做实事的人，很不幸的是…\N{\rENG}I see the people that do the real work,and what's really sad is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.48,0:27:19.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,…那些最慷慨的，最勤劳的…\N{\rENG}...the people that are the most giving, hardworking...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.22,0:27:21.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,…也是最能让这个世界变得更好的人…\N{\rENG}...and capable of making this world better...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.62,0:27:24.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,…往往没什么野心，不想成为什么领袖\N{\rENG}...usually don't have the ego and ambition to be a leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.96,0:27:27.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们对那些形式上的奖励没有兴趣\N{\rENG}They don't see any interest in superficial rewards.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.80,0:27:30.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们也不在乎自己的名字能不能上报纸\N{\rENG}They don't care if their name ever appear in the press.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.07,0:27:33.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们只是享受着帮助人的那种过程\N{\rENG}They actually enjoy the process of helping others.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.07,0:27:36.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 他们自得其乐  - 是啊，不过那很难啊！\N{\rENG}- They're in the moment.  - Yeah, but that's so hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.94,0:27:39.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,自得其乐，我是说，我感觉我好像…\N{\rENG}...you know, to be in the moment.I mean, I feel like I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.01,0:27:44.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,是被设计成那种对什么都不很满意的类型…\N{\rENG}...designed to be slightly dissatisfied with everything, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.18,0:27:46.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗，我是说，好像永远都在试图改善自己的现状一样\N{\rENG}It's like always trying to better my situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.91,0:27:50.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,我满足了一种欲望，就会刺激另一种欲望，懂吗？\N{\rENG}I satisfy one desire,and it just agitates another.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.52,0:27:54.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后我就想：都去他妈的吧，欲望是生活的动力\N{\rENG}And then I think, to hell with it, right?Desire's the fuel of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.26,0:27:57.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,你认为这是真的吗？\N{\rENG}You know? Do you think it's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.29,0:28:00.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果我们没有欲望，我们就会永远快乐？\N{\rENG}...that if we never wanted anything,we'd never be unhappy?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.43,0:28:05.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道，没有欲望，这难道不是抑郁症的一种表现吗？\N{\rENG}I don't know. Not wanting anything,isn't that a symptom of depression?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.63,0:28:09.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错，就是的，对吧？我是说，有欲望是种健康的表现，对吧？\N{\rENG}Yeah, that is, right?I mean, it's healthy to desire, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.47,0:28:13.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，我不知道，不过那些佛教徒都那么说，对吧？\N{\rENG}Yeah. I don't know. It's what all those Buddhist guys say, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.31,0:28:15.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,从欲望中解脱出来，你就会发现…\N{\rENG}Liberate yourself from desire,and you'll find...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.84,0:28:19.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你已经拥有你需要的一切  - 是啊，不过当我想要拥有…\N{\rENG}- ...you already have everything you need.  - But I feel alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.28,0:28:22.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,那些不算基本生存需要的东西的时候，我能感觉到自己是真实存活的\N{\rENG}...when I want something more than basic survival needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.22,0:28:25.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，不管哪种欲望，比如想和谁亲热\N{\rENG}Wanting, whether it's intimacy with another person...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.29,0:28:27.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,或是想要双新鞋，都很美…\N{\rENG}...or a pair of shoes, is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.22,0:28:30.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜欢我们拥有无止境的欲望\N{\rENG}I like that we have those ever-renewing desires, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.99,0:28:32.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,也许那是一种有权享用的感觉\N{\rENG}Maybe it's this sense of entitlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.93,0:28:36.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗，好像什么时候你觉得你配穿双新鞋\N{\rENG}You know, like whenever you feel like you deserve that new pair of shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.86,0:28:40.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,欲望本身不是坏事，只要你不要太在意得失就好\N{\rENG}It's okay to want things, as long as you aren't pissed off if you don't get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.94,0:28:42.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,生活很辛苦，这也是顺理成章的事\N{\rENG}Life's hard. It's supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.00,0:28:46.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,吃一堑，长一智，对吗？\N{\rENG}If we didn't suffer, we wouldn't learn a thing, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.38,0:28:49.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,那，你是佛教徒吗？\N{\rENG}So, what, are you Buddhist,or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.34,0:28:53.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不是  - 不是？为什么不是？\N{\rENG}- No.  - No? Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.45,0:28:58.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道，出于同一原因，我不会让自己完全相信任何信仰\N{\rENG}I don't know. The same reason I don't really consider myself anything, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.55,0:29:01.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,很久前我就决定，我可以接受任何信念…\N{\rENG}I decided a long time ago that I was gonna be open to everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.19,0:29:04.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是不会执迷于一种信仰\N{\rENG}...but not buy into any one and only belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.33,0:29:09.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,数年前，我曾经去过一所苦修派修道院\N{\rENG}I went to this Trappist monastery a couple years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.03,0:29:13.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 苦修派？ - 是的，天主教西多教派的\N{\rENG}- Trappist?  - Yeah, they're Catholic. Cistercian.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.17,0:29:17.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你为什么要去那  - 为什么？可能就是去读些书吧\N{\rENG}- Why did you do that?  - Why? I'd been doing some reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.01,0:29:21.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得那很酷，你曾经和修士和修女生活在一起过吗？\N{\rENG}Thought it'd be cool. Have you ever spent any time with monks or nuns?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.18,0:29:25.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没有，我可不想那样  - 没有？\N{\rENG}- No. It's not really my style.  - No?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.28,0:29:30.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我本来以为他们都是神情肃穆、严厉苛刻的，但是他们不是\N{\rENG}Well, I expected them to be all glowering and stern, but they weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.55,0:29:33.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们很容易就笑，非常好相处\N{\rENG}They were quick to laugh,really easy to be around.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.35,0:29:36.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,真的，他们对一切都不排斥，他们只是…\N{\rENG}Seriously, very attuned to everything,they were just...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.59,0:29:39.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗，他们不会打扰任何人\N{\rENG}You know, they weren't trying to hustle anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.23,0:29:41.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们只是想平静的信奉天主、生存，然后死去\N{\rENG}They're trying to live and die in peace with God...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.93,0:29:44.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,也或者他们信奉的是其他什么他们觉得永恒的东西\N{\rENG}...or whatever part of them they feel is eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.63,0:29:46.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是身处其间真的很舒服\N{\rENG}It was just so refreshing to be around.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.77,0:29:49.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗，你会发现你遇到的绝大多数人\N{\rENG}You realize that most of the people that you meet...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.44,0:29:51.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,都是想要过的更好\N{\rENG}...are trying to get somewhere better.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.41,0:29:54.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,赚更多的钱啦，赢得更多的尊敬啊，\N{\rENG}They're trying to make more cash,get a little more respect...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.81,0:29:57.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,让人们崇拜自己啊之类的，太累了！\N{\rENG}...have more people admire them.It's exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.45,0:30:00.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没错  - 要是你自己也成为这样的人，真是太累了\N{\rENG}- No kidding.  - And it's exhausting to be one yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.78,0:30:04.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，我就是这样的，精神上很贪婪\N{\rENG}There I am, right, you know,all greedy to be more spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.32,0:30:07.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想变得更好，懂吗，这是你逃不脱的！\N{\rENG}"I want to be a better person,"you know? You can't escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.09,0:30:14.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,好多年前，我有个男友想做佛教徒\N{\rENG}I had this boyfriend of mine many years ago that wanted to be a Buddhist.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.63,0:30:17.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后他去了亚洲，去瞻仰那里的寺院\N{\rENG}So he went to Asia to visit some of those monasteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.40,0:30:21.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是啊，我也想过去那些地方  - 那你应该去，我告诉你为什么\N{\rENG}- I've thought about doing that too.  - Yeah, you should. I'll tell you why.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.30,0:30:24.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,啊，他长得很帅，每次他去那些寺院的时候\N{\rENG}He was good-looking, and each time he went to one of the monasteries...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.84,0:30:27.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,都会有僧侣愿意替他口交\N{\rENG}...a monk offered to suck his cock.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.68,0:30:29.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,真的\N{\rENG}True story.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.84,0:30:32.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，最后都会变成这样，对吧？\N{\rENG}It all comes down to that, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.98,0:30:35.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，这就是为什么我很崇拜你做的事\N{\rENG}That's why I really admire what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.35,0:30:37.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你知道吗？ - 你什么意思，口交？\N{\rENG}- You know?  - What do you mean? Sucking cock?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.69,0:30:40.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 啊，不…  - 不是？我猜错了？\N{\rENG}- No.  - No? Wrong answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.06,0:30:44.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是，我想说的是，你不是那种超然的人\N{\rENG}No, I was gonna say you're not detached from life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.06,0:30:47.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,你做事很有激情\N{\rENG}You're putting your passion into action.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.66,0:30:50.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个嘛，起码我努力这样做\N{\rENG}Well, I'll try.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.97,0:30:54.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗，我接下来八个小时会在机场\N{\rENG}You know something?I'm gonna be on planes...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.50,0:30:56.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,以及飞机上度过\N{\rENG}...and in an airport for the next eight hours....
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.07,0:30:59.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很想再看看巴黎\N{\rENG}I'd just love to see a little bit more of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.71,0:31:01.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我们能出去走走…  - 好啊，好啊，我们走吧！\N{\rENG}- Would you walk with me?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.34,0:31:02.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你介意吗？ - 怎么会呢，很好啊！\N{\rENG}- Do you mind?  - That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.88,0:31:04.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你想去吗？ - 当然！\N{\rENG}- Do you want to?  - Let's do that. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.01,0:31:06.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们该付多少？四块五…\N{\rENG}What do we owe here?Four-fifty?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.08,0:31:09.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,不用，不用，我有，我有\N{\rENG}No, I got it, I got a little per diem going on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.78,0:31:12.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这够付小费的了吗？ - 嗯，够了\N{\rENG}- This good, for a tip?  - Yeah, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.22,0:31:14.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 只多不少！ - 这个也留下吧\N{\rENG}- That's more than enough.  - Throw that in too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.82,0:31:18.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好啦，周围有什么值得逛的吗？ - 今天是减价日！\N{\rENG}- Is there anywhere to go around here?  - It's sales day today.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.53,0:31:21.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么意思？ - 今天巴黎什么东西都会减价\N{\rENG}- What's that?  - It's when everything's "en solde" in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.96,0:31:23.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,每年两次\N{\rENG}It's twice a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.75,0:31:24.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}再见，谢谢\N{\rENG}Au revoir!Merci!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.55,0:31:25.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}再见\N{\rENG}Au revoir!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.87,0:31:27.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啊，那我们去购物吧！\N{\rENG}All right, let's go shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.70,0:31:30.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，不，这主意不好，我不想让你这样\N{\rENG}No, no, no. That's a bad idea.I don't wanna inflict that on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.04,0:31:34.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,那简直疯了，我们就去那个花园逛逛吧，那真的不错的\N{\rENG}It's madness. Let's just go to this garden path. It's really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.28,0:31:37.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啊，听起来其实比购物要好\N{\rENG}All right. That sounds better than shopping, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.88,0:31:40.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，我并不是不想陪你做你喜欢的事\N{\rENG}Not that I wouldn't do whatever you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.18,0:31:43.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,其实有的时候我也不是需要什么东西\N{\rENG}Sometimes I don't even need to buy anything. I just get high...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.35,0:31:45.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是想试穿，还有看那些商品，这让我很兴奋\N{\rENG}...on trying on and looking at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.32,0:31:47.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个嘛，苦修派僧侣会对你说…我们往这边走？\N{\rENG}Is this where we're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.25,0:31:49.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是的！ - 苦修派僧侣会对你说这很好\N{\rENG}- Yeah.  - A therapist will tell you that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.69,0:31:52.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真的？你节食过吗？ - 没有！\N{\rENG}- Really? Are you ever in therapy?  - Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.26,0:31:55.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我看起来像在节食吗？ - 我只是开玩笑\N{\rENG}- Do I seem like I'm in therapy?  - I'm kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.73,0:31:59.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这对你的性障碍有帮助吗？ - 我的性障碍？\N{\rENG}- Does it help your sex problems?  - My sex problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.73,0:32:01.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没有啦，我只是开玩笑  - 比如呢？跟我说实话\N{\rENG}- I'm kidding.  - Tell me the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.50,0:32:03.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那天晚上我们不是挺好的？ - 不，我是在开玩笑\N{\rENG}- We didn't have any problems.  - No, I'm kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.94,0:32:06.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我们根本就没有做爱  - 这是个玩笑，对吧？\N{\rENG}- We didn't even have sex.  - That's a joke, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.64,0:32:09.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是，我们确实没做爱！就是这么回事\N{\rENG}No, we didn't.I mean, that was the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.44,0:32:11.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 可我们确实做了啊！- 没有，没有，我们没做！\N{\rENG}- Of course we did.  - No, no, no, we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.71,0:32:14.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,你没有安全套，而我没有安全套从来不做爱\N{\rENG}You didn't have a condom and I never have sex without one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.72,0:32:16.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,尤其是一夜情那种，我是说，我对于自己的健康非常在意，我不可能…\N{\rENG}I'm extremely paranoid.There's no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.78,0:32:19.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得这太可怕了，你竟然不记得我们之间发生过什么\N{\rENG}I find it scary that you don't remember what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.52,0:32:20.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，听我说\N{\rENG}No, listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.06,0:32:23.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,…我从来没写过一整本书，但是我记日记…\N{\rENG}...I didn't write an entire book,but I kept a journal...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.96,0:32:25.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在里面记下了整晚发生的事\N{\rENG}...and I wrote the whole night in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.01,0:32:27.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就是我的意思，你对那夜进行了理想化的加工！\N{\rENG}That's what I meant, you idealizing it in night.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.10,0:32:31.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啦，听我说！我甚至记得我们用过的安全套是什么牌子的\N{\rENG}All right, listen, I even remember what brand of condom we used.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.53,0:32:33.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啦，这太恶心啦，我不想听！\N{\rENG}That's disgusting.I don't wanna hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.60,0:32:36.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这有什么恶心的…  - 没有啦\N{\rENG}- That's not disgusting.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.40,0:32:40.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啦，等我回家，我会查我九四年的日记，不过我知道我是对的！\N{\rENG}Okay, when I get home I'll check my journal from '94, but I know I'm right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.78,0:32:45.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 等等…  - 怎么了？\N{\rENG}- Wait a minute.  - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.88,0:32:48.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那是在一个墓地发生的吗？ - 不是…\N{\rENG}- Was it in the cemetery?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.82,0:32:51.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是的，我们是下午去那个墓地的\N{\rENG}No, we went to the cemetery in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.39,0:32:54.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,应该是在一个公园里，深夜时分\N{\rENG}It was in the park, very late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.69,0:32:56.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 在公园里！ - 等等…\N{\rENG}- In the park?  - Wait a minute, wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.99,0:32:58.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真不能…我没法…\N{\rENG}I can't... I can't....
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.76,0:33:03.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,这事这么容易忘记吗？你真的不记得了？在公园里！\N{\rENG}Is it that forgettable? You really don't remember? In the park?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.26,0:33:06.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，等等，我想你可能是对的…\N{\rENG}Okay. Wait a minute,I think you might be right...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.30,0:33:07.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,行啦，你在和我胡扯是不是\N{\rENG}You're messing with me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.84,0:33:09.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没有  - 你在和我胡扯吗？\N{\rENG}- No.  - Are you messing with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:12.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是的，对不起！我觉得你…我是说，你是对的，这样可以了吧？\N{\rENG}Okay. No, I'm sorry. I think... I mean, you're right, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.81,0:33:16.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,有时我就是忘事\N{\rENG}Sometimes I put things in drawers inside my head and forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.48,0:33:19.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想有时忘记会让人少些痛苦！\N{\rENG}It's less painful to put things away than live with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.35,0:33:22.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么，就是说那夜对你来说是段很难过的回忆罗？\N{\rENG}What, so that night was, like,a sad memory for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.28,0:33:24.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，我不是针对那一夜\N{\rENG}I didn't mean that night in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.29,0:33:26.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是说有些事情还是忘了好\N{\rENG}I meant certain things are better forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.59,0:33:29.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,那夜是我那一整年记的最清楚的一天\N{\rENG}I remember that night better than I do entire years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.29,0:33:31.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我也是  - 真的吗？\N{\rENG}- Me too.  - Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.26,0:33:33.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,呃，我觉得我是…\N{\rENG}Well, I thought I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.03,0:33:39.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过，可能我…可能我忘记那事是因为…\N{\rENG}But maybe I... Maybe I put it away because of the fact that...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.87,0:33:43.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,…我祖母葬礼的那天，就是我们约好再见的那天\N{\rENG}...my grandmother's funeral was the day we were supposed to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.24,0:33:46.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,对我来说那天挺难熬，不过对你来说大概更糟\N{\rENG}It was a tough day for me,but it must've been worse for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.37,0:33:50.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,感觉好像不真实，我还记得我看见她的遗体躺在棺材里\N{\rENG}It was unreal. I remember looking at her dead body in the coffin...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.15,0:33:55.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,她曾经总是用她美丽的手抱着我，那么温暖，那么亲切…\N{\rENG}...at her beautiful hands, so warm,so sweet, that used to hold me...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.02,0:33:59.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是棺材里的她，和我记忆中的一点都不一样\N{\rENG}...but nothing in that coffin resembled what I remembered of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.49,0:34:01.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有的温暖都消逝了\N{\rENG}All the warmth was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.32,0:34:04.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后我开始哭…我感觉很困惑，不知道\N{\rENG}And then I was crying,so confused if I was crying...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.29,0:34:09.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我哭是因为不能再见到她了，还是因为不能再见到你了\N{\rENG}...because I was never gonna see her again or never gonna see you again....
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.06,0:34:13.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,对不起，我竟然变成这样，这个星期我情绪都有点低落，我不知道…\N{\rENG}I'm sorry. I'm sorry to go on like this.I've been a little down this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.14,0:34:17.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 为什么？ - 我不知道，没什么，只是…\N{\rENG}- Why?  - I don't know. Nothing bad, just....
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.34,0:34:19.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,可能是因为读了你的书？\N{\rENG}Reading your book, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.47,0:34:23.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,也不是，不过…想想那个夏天和秋天，我充满了希望\N{\rENG}No, but... Thinking of how hopeful I was that summer and fall...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.54,0:34:25.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,而自从那以后，好像就有点…\N{\rENG}...and since then it's been kind of a....
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.35,0:34:27.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也不知道\N{\rENG}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.92,0:34:32.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,回忆本来是非常美好的，只要你能让过去的都过去\N{\rENG}Memory is a wonderful thing if you don't have to deal with the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.82,0:34:37.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,回忆本来是非常美好的，只要你能让过去的都过去\N{\rENG}"Memory is wonderful if you don't have to deal with the past."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.83,0:34:39.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,我能把这话贴到我车牌上吗？\N{\rENG}Can I put that on a bumper sticker?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.66,0:34:42.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗？要是你写一本关于我们的一夜情的书，这是个不错的书名！\N{\rENG}If you wrote a book about our night,that's a good title.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.53,0:34:46.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 可能会是本完全不同的书  - 是啊，不会涉及色情\N{\rENG}- And it could be a total different book.  - Yeah, there'd be no sex scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.00,0:34:48.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不过你知道吗？ - 嗯？\N{\rENG}- But you know what?  - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.54,0:34:49.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,既然现在我们又见面了\N{\rENG}Now that we've met again...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.10,0:34:52.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们可以改变我们那个十二月十六日的回忆\N{\rENG}...we can change our memory of that December 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.91,0:34:56.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,那回忆将不再有是以悲剧结尾了，因为我们又见面了\N{\rENG}It no longer has that sad ending of us never seeing each other again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.54,0:35:01.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错，我想回忆永远可以更改，只要你还活着…\N{\rENG}Right. I mean, I guess a memory's never finished as long as you're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.22,0:35:04.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，我知道，我有一段童年的回忆\N{\rENG}Yeah, I know. I have this memory from my childhood...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.02,0:35:07.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 但是我最近意识到，这段回忆其实从未发生过  - 是什么？\N{\rENG}- ...I realized recently never happened.  - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.76,0:35:10.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个，当我八九岁的时候，我妈妈很担心\N{\rENG}Well, when I was 8 or 9,my mom was so paranoid...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.89,0:35:13.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,…怕我上完钢琴课以后，一个人走回家会出事…\N{\rENG}...when I was walking home from my piano lesson at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.93,0:35:16.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,…她总是让我当心色迷迷的的老头给我糖果…\N{\rENG}...she'd warn me about dirty old men giving me candies...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.83,0:35:18.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,…然后给我看他们的鸡鸡\N{\rENG}...and then showing me their pee-pees.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.83,0:35:21.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,她总是这么说，然后后来，你懂吗，我…\N{\rENG}She was so obsessed with it that,later in life, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.07,0:35:25.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,…我头脑中就真的觉得这曾经发生过！\N{\rENG}...I had this image in my head that this really happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.64,0:35:29.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我甚至把做爱和回家联系到一起了\N{\rENG}To the point that I even associated sex with that walk home.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.38,0:35:33.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，有时候，甚至是现在，当我…\N{\rENG}I mean, and sometimes,even now, when I'm....
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.95,0:35:37.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,当我做爱的时候，我都好像看见我自己在那街上走\N{\rENG}When I'm having sex, I see myself walking down that street.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.09,0:35:39.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我发誓！非常奇怪，对吧？\N{\rENG}I swear. It's so weird, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.15,0:35:44.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 呃，那条街离这近吗？我是说，能…  - 不行\N{\rENG}- ls that street nearby? I mean, could...?  - Could we? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.56,0:35:46.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,非常远\N{\rENG}Very far.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.93,0:35:50.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,你小的时候记日记吗？\N{\rENG}Did you ever keep a journal when you were a kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.63,0:35:53.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯，算是吧，有时记\N{\rENG}Yeah. On and off, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.13,0:35:56.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,很有意思的是，我有天读了…\N{\rENG}It's funny, I read one of mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.47,0:35:58.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我八三年的一本日记  - 怎么了\N{\rENG}- ...from '83 the other day.  - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.67,0:36:00.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我惊奇的是\N{\rENG}And what really surprised me is...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.51,0:36:03.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我那时的人生观和现在一样\N{\rENG}...that I was dealing with life the same way I am now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.64,0:36:05.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然我那时更天真，更充满希望\N{\rENG}I was much more hopeful and naive...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.81,0:36:10.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,…不过内心深处对事情的感觉是完全一样的！\N{\rENG}...but the core, and the way I was feeling things, is exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.28,0:36:12.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,这让我意识到我其实没怎么变\N{\rENG}It made me realize I haven't changed much at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.79,0:36:14.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，谁不是这样的呢？\N{\rENG}I don't think anybody does.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.46,0:36:18.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,尽管人们都不愿意承认，但事实上我们…我们很多个性都是天生的\N{\rENG}People don't want to admit it, but it's like we have these innate set points...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.43,0:36:22.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,很少有什么后天发生的事能改变我们的性情\N{\rENG}...and nothing much that happens to us changes our disposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.20,0:36:23.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你是这么想的？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- You believe that?  - I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.83,0:36:27.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我曾经读过一些研究报告，是关于那些赢了彩票的人…\N{\rENG}I read this study where they followed people who'd won the lottery...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.33,0:36:29.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,…和截瘫的人的心态\N{\rENG}...and people who'd become paraplegics.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.40,0:36:33.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,你会认为前一件事能让你欣喜若狂，后一件则让你简直想自杀\N{\rENG}You'd think one extreme is gonna make you euphoric and the other suicidal.
