Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.93,0:42:02.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯，或是各种爱恨情仇…还有一首是写我的猫猫的！\N{\rENG}Relationships. One's about my cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.77,0:42:05.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 唱首听听！ - 不行，我没有吉他\N{\rENG}- Sing one.  - No, I can't. I don't have a guitar.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.44,0:42:07.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 来吧，清唱一首  - 不行，不行\N{\rENG}- Come on. A cappella.  - No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.17,0:42:10.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有吉他伴奏我唱不了歌，你太过分了！\N{\rENG}I'm not singing a song without a guitar.You're nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.84,0:42:12.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,为什么？\N{\rENG}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.95,0:42:15.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好吧，至少不是现在  - 就一首\N{\rENG}- No, okay. Not now. No.  - One.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.55,0:42:18.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果不是现在，还有什么时候呢？你想六个月后在这儿见面吗？带着吉他？\N{\rENG}If not now, when? You want to meet here in six months with a guitar?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.99,0:42:20.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我会飞过来的\N{\rENG}I'll fly all the way over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.65,0:42:23.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 但你不一定能赶上地铁  - 好啦，这不好笑\N{\rENG}- You may or may not make the Metro.  - Okay, that's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.02,0:42:26.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我们该回书店了！ - 没事的\N{\rENG}- We've got to get back.  - We'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.29,0:42:28.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你会错过你的航班的，快点！ - 好吧\N{\rENG}- You're gonna miss your flight.  - All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.46,0:42:30.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们可以沿塞纳河走走，很漂亮的\N{\rENG}We can walk down La Seine.It's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.46,0:42:32.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.63,0:42:36.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那你是要飞回纽约吗？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- So you're flying back to New York?  - Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.21,0:42:42.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在文章中读到你结婚了，还有了一个孩子，真是太好了！\N{\rENG}So I read in that article that you're married with a kid. That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.34,0:42:44.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错，他已经…他已经四岁了\N{\rENG}Yeah, he's... He's 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.01,0:42:47.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 他叫什么？ - 亨利，小汉克\N{\rENG}- What's his name?  - Henry. Little Hank.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.38,0:42:50.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 他很可爱  - 当然了\N{\rENG}- He's so much fun.  - Oh, wow, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.35,0:42:53.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你的太太呢？她是做什么的？ - 她在小学教书\N{\rENG}- Your wife, what does she do?  - She teaches elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.85,0:42:56.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你有孩子吗？ - 是的，有两个。糟了！\N{\rENG}- Do you have kids?  - Yes, two... Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.59,0:42:58.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 怎么了？ - 我把他们落在车上了！\N{\rENG}- What?  - I left them in the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.23,0:43:00.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,窗关得死死的，快有六个月了…他们会有事吗？\N{\rENG}With the windows up, six months ago!Think they're okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.06,0:43:03.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有啦，我开玩笑的，不过我很想要小孩\N{\rENG}No, I'm kidding.No, but I want to have kids someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.86,0:43:05.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 只是还没做好准备  - 没有吗？\N{\rENG}- I'm just not ready yet.  - No?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.90,0:43:09.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不过我现在正在认真谈恋爱  - 噢是吗？这很好啊\N{\rENG}- I'm in a good relationship, though.  - Oh yeah? That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.24,0:43:11.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 他是做什么的？ - 他是个摄影记者\N{\rENG}- What's he do?  - He's a photojournalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.51,0:43:13.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,专门做战地新闻\N{\rENG}He does war coverage.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.51,0:43:16.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,他经常出差，不过从某种角度对我来说，是一件好事，因为我实在是太忙了\N{\rENG}He's away a lot, which is good because I'm so busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.24,0:43:20.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过那不是很危险吗？我是说，不是有很多人在战争中丧生吗？\N{\rENG}But isn't that dangerous? Aren't a lot of those guys getting killed these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.51,0:43:23.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,他向我保证不会太冒险的，不过我还是会经常担心\N{\rENG}He promises me he doesn't take risks,but I often worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.92,0:43:26.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,他一拿起相机就什么都不顾了\N{\rENG}He goes in this trance when he photographs something.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.62,0:43:29.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么意思？ - 有一次我们在新德里\N{\rENG}- What do you mean?  - Well, once we were in New Delhi...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.12,0:43:31.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,见到一个流浪汉，他躺在人行道上\N{\rENG}...and we passed a bum on the...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.83,0:43:34.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 炸弹？{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[谐音]{\rCHS}  - 流浪汉！无家可归的人\N{\rENG}- A bomb?  - A bum. A homeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.23,0:43:35.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，流浪汉\N{\rENG}All right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.73,0:43:39.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,总之他看起来需要帮助，但是我男朋友的第一个反应就是拿起相机！\N{\rENG}He looked like he needed help, but his first reaction was to photograph him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.73,0:43:42.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,他凑到离那个人的脸非常近的地方整理他的衣领，让他看起来显得更精神\N{\rENG}He went really close to his face,fixing his collar...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.74,0:43:44.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,他似乎完全不在乎那个人\N{\rENG}...totally detached from the person.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.64,0:43:47.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过要做好工作不就得这样吗？\N{\rENG}But don't you have to be like that to be good at that job?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.57,0:43:48.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，我知道啊，我不是…\N{\rENG}Yeah, I mean, I'm not....
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.08,0:43:52.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不是由此来看他的为人，他的工作是重要的也是高尚的\N{\rENG}I'm not judging him.What he does is essential and incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.38,0:43:54.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是说这是我自己永远做不到的\N{\rENG}All I'm saying is that I could never do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.65,0:43:56.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们上那船吧！快！\N{\rENG}Let's get on that boat. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.58,0:43:57.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不！ - 快，很有趣的！\N{\rENG}- No!  - Come on, it'll be fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.09,0:44:00.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你没时间了！我们得走了  - 它就要开了\N{\rENG}- You don't have time!  - They're about to take off.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.59,0:44:02.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还有十五分钟呢，你有手机吗？\N{\rENG}I've got 15 more minutes.Do you have a cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.16,0:44:05.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 有  - 那就好，我有那个司机的号码\N{\rENG}- Yeah.  - All right, I've got that driver's number.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.66,0:44:07.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可以打电话给他，让他在下一站停船的地方接我们\N{\rENG}I can call him to pick us up at the next stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.99,0:44:11.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，可我从来没上过那船，这是给游客的，太丢脸了\N{\rENG}I've never been on those boats.It's for tourists, it's embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.07,0:44:13.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啦，没事的\N{\rENG}Okay. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.05,0:44:16.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}唔，我们可以上船了吗？ - 当然\N{\rENG}- Uhm, c'est bon?Pouvons-nous entrer?  - Bien sur!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.55,0:44:19.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}请给我两张票！ - 不，让我来，让我来\N{\rENG}- Deux tickets, s'il vous plait!  - No, I'll get it, I'll get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.25,0:44:21.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}不，不，还是我来吧  - 好吧，好吧，好吧\N{\rENG}- No, no, c'est bon.  - All right. All right, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.45,0:44:25.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}下一站停在哪里？ - {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}亨利四世码头\N{\rENG}- C'est ou qu'il s'arrete au prochain arret?  - C'est au Quai Henry IV.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.36,0:44:26.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.81,0:44:28.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那你现在是跟他沉浸在爱河里咯？ - 谁？\N{\rENG}- So are you in love with that guy?  - What guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.15,0:44:32.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那个战地摄影师  - 哦，当然！\N{\rENG}- The war photographer.  - Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.95,0:44:36.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}你们可以进去了  - 谢谢\N{\rENG}- Vous pouvez y aller.  - Merci.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.29,0:44:38.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,对不起，你的手机…\N{\rENG}So do you have that cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.66,0:44:40.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，对\N{\rENG}Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.59,0:44:42.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好，让我看看他的号码…  - 好\N{\rENG}- Okay, let's see....  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.60,0:44:43.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,我该怎么跟他说呢？\N{\rENG}What do I tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.10,0:44:46.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,让他在亨利四世码头等着\N{\rENG}Tell him to pick you up at Quai Henri Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.47,0:44:49.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，见鬼，什么码头？\N{\rENG}Oh, shit. Quai...?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.44,0:44:52.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,亨利四世，亨利四世码头\N{\rENG}Henri Quatre. Quai Henri Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.41,0:44:54.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,亨利四世\N{\rENG}Henri Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.61,0:44:57.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,你怎么了？不对，你要我来说吗？亨利四世\N{\rENG}What's wrong with you? No, do you want me to...? Henri Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.78,0:44:59.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 亨利四世？ - 没错！\N{\rENG}- Henry Four?  - Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.31,0:45:02.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那你为什么不直接说？ - 对不起！\N{\rENG}- Come on, why didn't you say so?  - I'm sorry. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.46,0:45:16.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,你好，是菲利普吗？\N{\rENG}Yeah, is this Philippe?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.53,0:45:19.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,菲利普，我是杰西·华莱士\N{\rENG}Yeah. Philippe, this is Jesse Wallace.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.37,0:45:20.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.93,0:45:25.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,呃，听我说，我现在在一条游船上\N{\rENG}Well, listen, I'm on one of those boats, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.34,0:45:28.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们将会在亨利四世码头下船\N{\rENG}And we're gonna arrive at Henry Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.44,0:45:31.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,亨利四号码头，你知道在哪儿吗？\N{\rENG}At Port Henry Four.You know what that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.98,0:45:34.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,很好，你带着我的行李吧？\N{\rENG}All right, great.And you have my bags, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.65,0:45:37.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们再过…总之下一站就到了\N{\rENG}Yeah, so we'll be there in... I don't know, it's the next stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.75,0:45:40.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,好，再见\N{\rENG}Okay. Au revoir.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.22,0:45:43.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 安排好了？ - 嗯\N{\rENG}- It's okay?  - Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.86,0:45:45.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,哇！\N{\rENG}Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.99,0:45:48.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 看这边啊，巴黎圣母院！ - 哇\N{\rENG}- Notre Dame, man. Check that out.  - Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.86,0:45:52.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,我听过一个故事，说的是占领巴黎的德军\N{\rENG}I heard this story once about when the Germans were occupying Paris...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.03,0:45:54.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,…撤出的时候\N{\rENG}...and they had to retreat back.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.84,0:45:56.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们在巴黎圣母院埋了很多炸药\N{\rENG}They wired Notre Dame to blow...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.97,0:46:01.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,…但他们得留一个人来按爆破的按钮\N{\rENG}...but they had to leave one guy in charge of hitting the switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.37,0:46:04.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,但那个人，那个士兵，他却下不了手！\N{\rENG}And the guy, the soldier,he couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.61,0:46:08.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,他只是呆呆地坐着，惊叹这地方的美妙\N{\rENG}He just sat there, knocked out by how beautiful the place was.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.52,0:46:10.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,当盟军部队到达的时候\N{\rENG}Then, when the Allied troops came in...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.55,0:46:14.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们发现炸药还在那里，但按钮没人碰过\N{\rENG}...they found all the explosives lying there and the switch unturned...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.22,0:46:17.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,同样的情景还发生在圣心堂，埃菲尔铁塔…\N{\rENG}...and they found the same thing at the Sacre-Coeur, Eiffel Tower...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.06,0:46:20.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,…很多地方\N{\rENG}...couple other places, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.53,0:46:22.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是真的吗？\N{\rENG}Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.63,0:46:25.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道，不过我一直很喜欢这个故事\N{\rENG}I don't know.I always liked the story, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.90,0:46:27.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错，很震撼的一个故事\N{\rENG}Yeah, that's a great story.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.50,0:46:30.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,你相信巴黎圣母院有一天会消失吗？\N{\rENG}But you have to think that Notre Dame will be gone one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.54,0:46:33.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,这里曾经是另一座教堂，就在这\N{\rENG}There used to be another church at the Seine, right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.87,0:46:36.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么，同一个地方？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- What, right in the same spot?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.14,0:46:40.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样好舒服，我从来没有试过！\N{\rENG}You know, this is great.I've never done this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.78,0:46:43.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是啊  - 我已经忘了巴黎有多美\N{\rENG}- Yeah.  - I forget about how beautiful Paris is.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.58,0:46:45.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,其实当个游客也不错\N{\rENG}It's not so bad, being a tourist.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.39,0:46:47.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢你带我上这船  - 不用客气\N{\rENG}- Thanks for getting me on the boat.  - You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.05,0:46:50.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得我在写那本书的时候，就好像在造什么东西\N{\rENG}I think that book that I wrote was like building something...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.46,0:46:55.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,以免我忘记我们经历过点点滴滴\N{\rENG}...so that I wouldn't forget the details of the time that we spent together.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.83,0:46:59.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗，就好像一个备忘录，告诉我我们的确见过面\N{\rENG}You know, like, just as a reminder,that once, we really did meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.77,0:47:02.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗，那是真的，真的发生过\N{\rENG}You know, that this was real,this happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.90,0:47:04.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很高兴你这么说，因为…\N{\rENG}I'm happy you're saying that,because....
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.07,0:47:09.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，我觉得自己很没用，因为我从来不能这么洒脱\N{\rENG}I mean, I always feel like a freak because I'm never able to move on like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.48,0:47:13.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,人们只是随意留情，甚至即使是认真的感情\N{\rENG}People just have an affair,or even entire relationships...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.98,0:47:16.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,…人们也会分手，然后忘记\N{\rENG}...they break up and they forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.55,0:47:20.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像换另一个牌子的麦片一样简单\N{\rENG}They move on like they would have changed brand of cereals.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.05,0:47:24.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,可我觉得我永远忘不了跟我交往过的每一个人\N{\rENG}I feel I was never able to forget anyone I've been with...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.46,0:47:30.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,…因为他们每个人都有很不一样的特质\N{\rENG}...because each person had their own specific qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.20,0:47:35.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不能取代任何人，失去的就失去了\N{\rENG}You can never replace anyone.What is lost is lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.20,0:47:40.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,每段感情结束的时候我都很受伤，我从来没有完全恢复过\N{\rENG}Each relationship, when it ends,really damages me. I never fully recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.57,0:47:43.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我尽量避免介入感情\N{\rENG}That's why I'm very careful with getting involved...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.88,0:47:45.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,…因为那种痛真的是太深了！\N{\rENG}...because it hurts too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.11,0:47:49.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,即使是做爱！其实我不喜欢那样\N{\rENG}Even getting laid,I actually don't do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.45,0:47:52.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为我会很怀念一个人很平常的东西\N{\rENG}...because I will miss of the person the most mundane things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.52,0:47:55.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,好比那些细节\N{\rENG}Like I'm obsessed with little things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.59,0:47:57.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者也许我有点神经质，但当我小的时候…\N{\rENG}Maybe I'm crazy,but when I was a little girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.09,0:48:00.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,妈妈告诉我，我上学经常迟到\N{\rENG}...my mom told me that I was always late to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.16,0:48:03.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,有一天她跟着我想知道为什么\N{\rENG}One day she followed me to see why.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.73,0:48:08.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,我正看着栗子从树上掉下来，滚到便道上\N{\rENG}I was looking at chestnuts falling from the trees, rolling on the sidewalk...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.20,0:48:13.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,…或者是蚂蚁过马路，叶子在树干上的映出的倒影\N{\rENG}...or ants crossing the road, the way a leaf casts a shadow on a tree trunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.14,0:48:16.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,种种小事\N{\rENG}Little things.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.68,0:48:18.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想对人也是一样\N{\rENG}I think it's the same with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.01,0:48:21.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我看到的是他们的细节，很细微\N{\rENG}I see in them little details,so specific to each of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.12,0:48:26.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,…那些能感动我的细节，然后我就会想念他们，一直想念\N{\rENG}...that move me and that I miss and will always miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.39,0:48:27.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不能取代任何人\N{\rENG}You can never replace anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.05,0:48:32.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为每个人都有他那种美丽的，独特的细微之处\N{\rENG}...because everyone is made of such beautiful, specific details.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.50,0:48:38.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,就好像我记得，你的胡子上有一点红色\N{\rENG}Like, I remember the way your beard has a bit of red in it...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.53,0:48:42.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,…我记得你离开的那天早上…\N{\rENG}...and how the sun was making it glow...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.40,0:48:45.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,…朝阳是怎样照的它闪闪亮\N{\rENG}...that morning right before you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.14,0:48:50.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一直记着，我非常怀念\N{\rENG}I remembered that, and I missed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.21,0:48:51.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,很神经质，对吧？\N{\rENG}Really crazy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.18,0:48:56.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在我明白了，你想知道为什么我写了那本烂书吗？\N{\rENG}Now I know for sure. You wanna know why I wrote that stupid book?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.28,0:48:59.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 为什么？ - 因为这样你就会参加巴黎的一场读者见面会\N{\rENG}- Why?  - So you'd come to a reading in Paris...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.42,0:49:03.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而我就可以走过去，问你：“你到底去哪里了？”\N{\rENG}...and I could walk up to you and ask,"Where the fuck were you? "
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.02,0:49:06.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你真的觉得我今天会来？\N{\rENG}No... You think I'd be here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.39,0:49:10.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,真的，我之所以写这本书，从某种意义来讲，就是为了能找到你\N{\rENG}I'm serious. I think I wrote it,in a way, to try to find you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.16,0:49:13.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啦，这…我知道这不是真的\N{\rENG}Okay, that's... I know that's not true...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.40,0:49:15.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不过听了还是很高兴  - 我觉得这是真的\N{\rENG}- ...but that's sweet of you.  - I think it is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.94,0:49:18.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们还有机会再见面吗？\N{\rENG}What were the chances of us ever meeting again?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.21,0:49:22.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,过了那个十二月，我想机率基本就是零了吧\N{\rENG}After that December,I'd say almost zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.81,0:49:24.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过反正我们也不是来真的，对吗？\N{\rENG}But we're not real anyway, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.05,0:49:28.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们只不过是那个老妇人梦中的角色\N{\rENG}We're just characters in that old lady's dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.42,0:49:30.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,她在她的病床上回忆年轻时的故事\N{\rENG}She's on her deathbed,fantasizing about her youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.98,0:49:33.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我们当然会见面！\N{\rENG}So of course we had to meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.25,0:49:37.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,天哪！你为什么那天没有出现在维也纳？\N{\rENG}Oh, God. Why weren't you there in Vienna?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.32,0:49:42.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我告诉过你了！ - 我知道，但是…\N{\rENG}- I told you why.  - I know why, I just....
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.26,0:49:44.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真的希望你去了！\N{\rENG}I wish you would have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.70,0:49:46.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们的生活可能会完全不一样！\N{\rENG}Our lives might have been so much different.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.10,0:49:49.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,你真这么觉得？\N{\rENG}You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.47,0:49:51.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rENG}I actually do.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.30,0:49:54.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,也许不会呢，也许最后我们会憎恨对方呢\N{\rENG}Maybe not. Maybe we would have hated each other eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.64,0:49:57.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,是吗，就像现在我们这样憎恨对方？\N{\rENG}What, like we hate each other now?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.45,0:50:02.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道的，可能我们…我们只适合那种偶遇…\N{\rENG}You know, maybe we're... We're only good at brief encounters...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.12,0:50:07.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,…在温暖的天气里，漫步在欧洲的街头\N{\rENG}...walking around in European cities,in warm climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.82,0:50:10.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,天哪，为什么我们没有交换电话号码呢？\N{\rENG}Oh, God. Why didn't we exchange phone numbers and stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.12,0:50:13.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,为什么？\N{\rENG}Why didn't we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.46,0:50:15.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为那时我们太年轻，不成熟？\N{\rENG}Because we were young and stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.00,0:50:18.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,你觉得我们现在还是如此吗？\N{\rENG}Do you think we still are?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.47,0:50:20.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得，当你年轻的时候，你会相信…\N{\rENG}I guess when you're young you just believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.77,0:50:23.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,…你会认识很多人\N{\rENG}...there'll be many people you'll connect with.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.97,0:50:26.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,但后来你才会发现能交流的人其实很少\N{\rENG}Later in life you realize it only happens a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.77,0:50:30.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,何况你又不能保证和他们好好相处，就这样，失去联系了\N{\rENG}And you can screw it up, you know.Misconnect.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.61,0:50:33.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,过去的就让它过去吧，事情本来就是这样的\N{\rENG}The past is the past.It was meant to be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.18,0:50:35.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,你真的相信吗？任何事情都是注定的？\N{\rENG}You really believe that?That everything's fated?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.02,0:50:40.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个嘛，你明白吗，世界也许没有我们想的那么多变\N{\rENG}Well, you know, the world might be less free than we think.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.19,0:50:41.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,是吗？\N{\rENG}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.16,0:50:46.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果给定了特定的条件，就总会发生一样的结果\N{\rENG}When given these exact circumstances,that's what will happen every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.26,0:50:49.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,两份氢，一份氧，获得的总是水\N{\rENG}Two part hydrogen, one part oxygen,you'll get water every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.46,0:50:52.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，我是说如果你祖母晚去世一个礼拜呢？\N{\rENG}No, I mean, what if your grandmother had lived a week longer, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.03,0:50:55.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者是早一个礼拜去世？甚至是几天？\N{\rENG}Or passed away a week earlier?Days, even?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.84,0:50:57.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,事情都可能完全不一样！我坚信这一点！\N{\rENG}Things might have been different.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.57,0:51:01.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不，你不能这样想，那只是…  - 我知道对于大多数事情来说的确是注定的\N{\rENG}- You can't think like that, it's...  - You shouldn't on most things, but....
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.98,0:51:07.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是，只是这件事，我觉得这事很不对劲\N{\rENG}It's just, on this one, it seemed like something was off, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.68,0:51:11.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗，在我结婚前的那个月，我一直都在想着你\N{\rENG}In the months leading up to my wedding,I was thinking about you all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.58,0:51:15.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,即使在去婚礼的路上，我坐在车里，我的一个朋友送我进城\N{\rENG}Even on my way there, I'm in the car, a buddy of mine is driving me downtown...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.59,0:51:18.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,…我看着窗户，觉得我看到你了\N{\rENG}...and I'm staring out the window and I think I see you...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.53,0:51:20.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,…离教堂不远…\N{\rENG}...not far from the church, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.86,0:51:23.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,…收起一把雨伞，走进一家熟食店…\N{\rENG}...folding up an umbrella and walking into a deli...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.53,0:51:27.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,…就在百老汇和十三街的交汇处\N{\rENG}...on the corner of 13th and Broadway.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.33,0:51:30.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,那时我觉得我快要发疯了你知道吗？但现在我觉得这也许就是你\N{\rENG}And I thought I was going crazy.But now I think it probably was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.67,0:51:34.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,我住在百老汇和十一街的交汇处\N{\rENG}I lived on 11 th and Broadway.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.07,0:51:36.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看！\N{\rENG}You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.24,0:51:42.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,那，结婚的感觉怎样，你还没说呢\N{\rENG}So, what is it like to be married?You haven't talked much about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.92,0:51:46.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没有吗？真奇怪\N{\rENG}I haven't? How weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.95,0:51:50.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道怎么说，我们是在上大学的时候认识的\N{\rENG}I don't know. We met, you know,when I was in college.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.09,0:51:57.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,有几年，我们分分合合，然后…\N{\rENG}And we broke up and got back together for a period of years, and then....
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.10,0:52:02.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么来着？我们好像又在一起了，然后她就怀孕了…\N{\rENG}What? We were sort of back together and she was pregnant...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.97,0:52:04.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以就结婚咯\N{\rENG}...so marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.74,0:52:06.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,她怎么样？\N{\rENG}What is she like?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.94,0:52:09.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,她是个好老师，好妈妈\N{\rENG}She's a great teacher, a good mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.14,0:52:13.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,她很聪明，很漂亮\N{\rENG}She's smart, pretty, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.38,0:52:15.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得那时我想…\N{\rENG}I remember thinking at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.62,0:52:17.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,…很多我所崇拜的人…\N{\rENG}...that so many of the men that I admired most...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.15,0:52:22.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,…他们的生命都奉献给了比自己更重要的东西\N{\rENG}...that their lives were dedicated to something greater than themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.76,0:52:26.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以你结婚是因为你崇拜的人都结婚了？\N{\rENG}So you got married because men you admired were married?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.63,0:52:32.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，不…准确来说是…我内心中有种对自我的完美期许\N{\rENG}No, no. It's more like I had this... This idea of my best self, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.07,0:52:34.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗？我想去追求那种自我\N{\rENG}And I wanted to pursue that...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.97,0:52:37.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,即使代价是失去真实的自我！\N{\rENG}...even if it might have been overriding my honest self.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.90,0:52:39.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂我的意思吗？\N{\rENG}You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.47,0:52:44.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得在那个时候，我并不觉得和“谁”结婚这个问题很重要\N{\rENG}In the moment, I remember thinking it didn't much matter, the who of it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.24,0:52:46.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个人并不是你生命的全部\N{\rENG}I mean, that nobody is gonna be everything to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.91,0:52:49.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,…到头来这只是一种负责的表现…\N{\rENG}...and that it's just the action of committing yourself...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.95,0:52:53.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,…就是说，负担起你的责任来，这才是最重要的\N{\rENG}...you know, meeting your responsibilities, that matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.62,0:52:57.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，爱是什么？如果它不是尊敬，信赖和钦佩的话？\N{\rENG}I mean, what is love, right,if it's not respect, trust, admiration?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.42,0:53:00.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我当时都感觉到了啊\N{\rENG}And I... I felt all those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.66,0:53:03.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,谈到现在，我感觉我好像在办一个托儿所\N{\rENG}Cut to the present,and I feel like I'm running a nursery...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.70,0:53:06.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,…跟一个我曾经约会过的人\N{\rENG}...with somebody I used to date you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.53,0:53:08.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，我就像一个修道士\N{\rENG}I mean, I'm like a monk, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.53,0:53:13.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在过去的四年中，做爱还不到十次\N{\rENG}I mean, I've had sex less than 10 times in the last four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.94,0:53:16.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 干嘛，干嘛？你笑我？ - 没有\N{\rENG}- What, what? You laughing at me?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.68,0:53:19.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 听起来很可悲吗？ - 你看到过有修道士做过十次爱的吗？\N{\rENG}- It sounds pathetic?  - What monastery do monks have sex...?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.68,0:53:23.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,好，你是对的，我比一般的修道士强，可以了吧？\N{\rENG}Okay, you're right, I'm doing better than most monks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.18,0:53:25.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我的确觉得，如果现在有人碰我的话\N{\rENG}But I do, I feel like if somebody were to touch me...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.85,0:53:28.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就会马上融化的了\N{\rENG}...I would dissolve into molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.22,0:53:30.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啦，我们到了，该走了，快\N{\rENG}Well, we're here. We've gotta go.Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.16,0:53:33.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,该死\N{\rENG}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.23,0:53:41.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}晚上好  - {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}晚上好\N{\rENG}- Bonsoir!  - Bonsoir!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.54,0:53:48.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我很遗憾听到那些  - 什么？\N{\rENG}- I'm sorry to hear that, you know.  - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.68,0:53:51.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你对你的婚姻好像不怎么满意\N{\rENG}You're not that happy with your marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.95,0:53:54.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我刚才说到的那个朋友，她是神经科医生  - 她怎么了？\N{\rENG}- This friend of mine, she's a shrink...  - How's she doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.75,0:53:56.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,她的生活很糟，不过…\N{\rENG}She's a mess, but....
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.52,0:53:59.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,她告诉我她遇过很多夫妻…\N{\rENG}No, she said she's been dealing with couples that are breaking up...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.95,0:54:02.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 为了同样的理由而分开  - 什么理由？\N{\rENG}- ...for the same reason.  - What reason is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.26,0:54:05.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们都期望，在共同生活了几年以后\N{\rENG}They all expected, after a few years of living together...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.19,0:54:07.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,…他们的热情，欲望还和当初一样\N{\rENG}...for the passion, that desire,to be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.69,0:54:09.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这是不可能的！ - 是啊，没错\N{\rENG}- Yeah, right.  - It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.33,0:54:10.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,而且谢天谢地…\N{\rENG}And thank God...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.83,0:54:14.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,…如果我们一直保持激情的话，我们会得动脉瘤的\N{\rENG}...we'd end up with aneurysms in that constant state of excitement, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.73,0:54:16.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们一生将一事无成\N{\rENG}We'd do nothing at all with our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.70,0:54:20.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你每五分钟就做一次爱，你还能写完你的书吗？\N{\rENG}Would you have finished your book if you were fucking every five minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.37,0:54:22.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很乐意接受这个挑战\N{\rENG}I might have welcomed the challenge,I mean....
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.18,0:54:25.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是，你懂吗，很自然的，当你太太生了小孩以后\N{\rENG}It's natural for your wife after the birth of your son...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.08,0:54:28.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 她就会把她的爱转移到小孩身上  - 当然\N{\rENG}- ...to give all her love to the little one.  - Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.88,0:54:32.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,想想看如果她执迷于性爱，像野猫一样不停挑逗你\N{\rENG}If she was obsessed with sex,riding you like a wildcat....
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.22,0:54:33.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,这不合情理，对吧？\N{\rENG}That wouldn't make any sense, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.12,0:54:37.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是这样的，你说得都很有道理，但这不是性的问题\N{\rENG}Everything you're saying makes sense.It's not about sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.89,0:54:40.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，我知道，很明显不是\N{\rENG}No, I know. It's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.26,0:54:41.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我…\N{\rENG}I....
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.00,0:54:46.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道，现在的夫妻感情很复杂\N{\rENG}You know, couples are so confused lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.37,0:54:48.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得肯定是因为…\N{\rENG}I think it must be that...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.80,0:54:52.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,…男人总想让人觉得他们很重要，但事实已不是这样了\N{\rENG}...men need to feel essential and they don't anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.94,0:54:55.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,多年以来，这种观念深植于他们脑海之中…\N{\rENG}It's been imprinted in their head for so many years...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.64,0:54:57.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,…好像他们就必须要是家里的顶梁柱\N{\rENG}...that they had to be the provider.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.54,0:55:01.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,比如，我在工作中就是一个坚强，独立的女性\N{\rENG}Like, I'm a strong, independent woman in my professional life.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.38,0:55:02.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不需要一个男人养我\N{\rENG}I don't need a man to feed me...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.08,0:55:06.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,…但我仍要一个男人爱我，而我也爱他\N{\rENG}...but I still need a man to love me and that I could love.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.79,0:55:10.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好啦，我看到你的司机了  - 是的\N{\rENG}- So your driver's here.  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.66,0:55:12.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,那，我想我该告别了\N{\rENG}Well, I guess this is goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.53,0:55:14.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你最好把你的…  - 不\N{\rENG}- You better give me your...  - No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.33,0:55:16.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们不如送你回家吧\N{\rENG}Why don't we just give you a ride home?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.73,0:55:19.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这个嘛，我可以搭地铁，我没事  - 不，我…\N{\rENG}- Well, I can take the Metro. I'm fine.  - No, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.23,0:55:22.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的飞机要十点才飞，我会提前两个钟头去\N{\rENG}My flight's not until 10.I'll be arriving two hours early.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.34,0:55:23.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样我们就可以继续谈了\N{\rENG}This way we can keep talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.94,0:55:26.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 先生，能…？ - 那不顺路的\N{\rENG}- Monsieur, can...?  - It's not on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.35,0:55:30.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}您能把我带到马场附近的十号路吗？\N{\rENG}Ca vous arrive me deposer au passage Dix Rue des petits ecuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.15,0:55:31.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}当然可以\N{\rENG}Oui, oui.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.45,0:55:33.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}我们走吧  - {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}麻烦您了\N{\rENG}- Allons-y!  - Ca peut etre trop tard?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.75,0:55:35.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}不，不，没问题\N{\rENG}No, no, ce n'est pas de probleme!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.25,0:55:38.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}您就把我带到“水塔”地铁站附近就行了\N{\rENG}Vous pouvez me laisser au metro...au metro Chateau d'Eau.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.25,0:55:40.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}好吗？ - {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}好的，没问题\N{\rENG}- Ca ira tres bien.  - Entendu!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.25,0:55:40.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}谢谢\N{\rENG}Merci!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.82,0:55:42.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,你把你的住址什么的都告诉他了？\N{\rENG}You told him where you are and all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.92,0:55:44.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.86,0:55:50.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 他知道他要去哪了？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- He knows where he's going?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.50,0:55:52.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,太好了\N{\rENG}Glad somebody does.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.57,0:55:56.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这比搭地铁好，对吧？ - 当然\N{\rENG}- But this is better than the Metro, right?  - Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.11,0:56:03.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在想，对我来说，还是不要把事情想得太浪漫比较好\N{\rENG}I was thinking, for me it's better I don't romanticize things as much anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.68,0:56:05.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一直都吃这个亏\N{\rENG}I was suffering so much all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.71,0:56:09.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我仍旧有很多梦想，但它们都与我的感情生活无关\N{\rENG}I still have lots of dreams,but they're not in regard to my love life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.45,0:56:11.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样并不会让我不开心，因为事情本来就是这样的\N{\rENG}It doesn't make me sad,it's just the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.02,0:56:16.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就是你为什么要和一个不常见面的人发生感情吗？\N{\rENG}Is that why you're in a relationship with somebody who's never around?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.32,0:56:20.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然，我应付不了那种天天见面的感情\N{\rENG}Yes, obviously I can't deal with the day-to-day life of a relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.39,0:56:22.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们相聚的时候可以充满激情\N{\rENG}Yeah, we have this exciting time together...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.66,0:56:26.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,…然后他离去了，我会很想他，不过我起码不会痛不欲生\N{\rENG}...and he leaves and I miss him,but at least I'm not dying inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.20,0:56:28.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果有人一直在我身边，我会觉得窒息！\N{\rENG}When someone's always around me,I'm suffocating.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.84,0:56:31.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,等等，可是你刚说你想要爱和被爱\N{\rENG}No, wait, you just said that you need to love and be loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.90,0:56:34.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错，但是当我的确这么做时，这马上会让我恶心！\N{\rENG}Yeah, but when I do,it quickly makes me nauseous.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.91,0:56:36.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,真是个灾难\N{\rENG}It's a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.54,0:56:39.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说，我只有一个人独处的时候才会真正开心\N{\rENG}I mean, I'm really happy only when I'm on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.38,0:56:44.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,即使是一个人，也比坐在情人边上却心不在焉要来的好\N{\rENG}Even being alone, it's better than sitting next to a lover and feeling lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.92,0:56:46.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,浪漫对我来说并不是一件容易的事\N{\rENG}It's not so easy for me to be a romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.02,0:56:50.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,你开始的时候可能会这么做，不过当你受过几次伤以后…\N{\rENG}You start off that way, and after you've been screwed over a few times...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.69,0:56:55.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,…你就会拒绝那些虚幻的想法，接受生活中的现实\N{\rENG}...you forget about your delusional ideas and you take what comes into your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.70,0:56:58.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,其实这也不见得对，我并没受过几次伤…\N{\rENG}That's not even true.I haven't been screwed over...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.36,0:57:00.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,…我只是有太多平庸的感情了\N{\rENG}...I've just had too many blah relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.93,0:57:02.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们不是对我不好，他们都很关心我…\N{\rENG}They weren't mean,they cared for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.94,0:57:06.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,…但是我们却没有那种心灵上的沟通，或是发自心底的兴奋\N{\rENG}...but there were no real connection or excitement.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.64,0:57:08.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,起码我这边是这么感觉的\N{\rENG}At least, not from my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.94,0:57:11.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,天哪，真遗憾，有这么糟糕吗？\N{\rENG}God, I'm sorry, is it really that bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.78,0:57:13.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有吧，对吗？\N{\rENG}It's not, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.08,0:57:17.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗，其实也不是这样的，我…\N{\rENG}You know, it's not even that.I was....
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.02,0:57:21.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,我本来是好好的，直到我读到你那本该死的书\N{\rENG}I was fine until I read your fucking book.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.69,0:57:23.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,它把陈年往事又翻起来了，你知道吗？\N{\rENG}It stirred shit up, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.72,0:57:26.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,它让我想起了，我曾经真正的浪漫过\N{\rENG}It reminded me how genuinely romantic I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.53,0:57:28.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,…我对于世界有过多少希望…\N{\rENG}...how I had so much hope in things...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.86,0:57:32.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而我现在已经完全不相信任何爱情了\N{\rENG}...and now it's like I don't believe in anything that relates to love.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.57,0:57:34.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我已经感觉不到人之间的感情了\N{\rENG}I don't feel things for people anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.70,0:57:39.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,从某种意义上来说，我所有的浪漫都在一夜之间消耗光了…\N{\rENG}In a way, I put all my romanticism into that one night...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.54,0:57:42.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而我将永远不可能再有那种感觉了\N{\rENG}...and I was never able to feel all this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.21,0:57:44.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,就好像，那一夜不知道怎么，引发了我的全部感情…\N{\rENG}Like, somehow this night took things away from me...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.91,0:57:47.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而我把这些感情都向你倾诉出来，而你却把它们都从我身边带走了\N{\rENG}...and I expressed them to you,and you took them with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.48,0:57:49.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,这让我感到孤独！好像爱情再也不属于我一样！\N{\rENG}It made me feel cold,like love wasn't for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.55,0:57:52.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不相信，我不相信\N{\rENG}I don't believe that.I don't believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.55,0:57:57.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗？对我来说，现实和爱基本就是矛盾的\N{\rENG}You know what? Reality and love are almost contradictory for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.96,0:58:02.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,非常可笑，我每一个以前的男友，他们都结婚了\N{\rENG}It's funny, every single of my exes,they're now married.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.43,0:58:05.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,男人约我出去，然后我们分手，然后他们就结婚了\N{\rENG}Men go out with me, we break up,and then they get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.50,0:58:08.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,之后之后他们打电话感谢我，教会了他们什么是爱\N{\rENG}And later they call me to thank me for teaching them what love is...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.20,0:58:11.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,…教会了他们去关心跟尊重女人！\N{\rENG}...and that I taught them to care and respect women.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.84,0:58:14.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我想我也是那些男人中的一个  - 你知道吗，我真想杀了他们！\N{\rENG}- I think I'm one of those.  - I want to kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.44,0:58:18.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们为什么不向我求婚？我也许会拒绝，但至少他们也应该问我啊！\N{\rENG}Why didn't they ask me? I would have said no, but they could have asked!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.24,0:58:22.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我知道这是我的错，因为我总觉得他们不是我的如意郎君\N{\rENG}I know it's my fault because I never felt it was the right man.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.25,0:58:25.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,从来没有，但如意的人又是什么呢？你的真爱？\N{\rENG}Never. But what does it mean,the right man, the love of your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.62,0:58:28.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,这种想法简直可笑，说什么我们只有找到了另一半人生才是完整的\N{\rENG}The concept is absurd. We can only be complete with another person.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.16,0:58:31.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这太可恶了，不是吗？ - 我能说两句吗？\N{\rENG}- It's evil, right?  - Can I talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.72,0:58:35.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想我是伤心过太多次了，然后又恢复了\N{\rENG}I guess I've been heartbroken too many times and then I recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.29,0:58:37.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,于是现在，从一开始，我就不愿意付出努力\N{\rENG}So now, you know, from the starts,I make no effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.10,0:58:40.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 因为我知道一定不能成功  - 你不能这样\N{\rENG}- I know it's not gonna work out.  - You can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.10,0:58:42.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不可以只是为了避免受伤害\N{\rENG}You can't live trying to avoid pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.17,0:58:44.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 就付出…  - 好啦，我决定了\N{\rENG}- ...at the expense...  - Those are words.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.14,0:58:46.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要离你远远的\N{\rENG}I've gotta get away from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.81,0:58:48.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 停车，我要下车！ - 不，别下车\N{\rENG}- Stop the car, I wanna get out.  - No, don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.14,0:58:51.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你知道在你身边…  - 请继续讲…\N{\rENG}- Keep talking.  - It's being around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.18,0:58:53.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,别碰我！你知道吗，我要叫辆计程车…\N{\rENG}Don't touch me, you know.I want to get on a cab.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.75,0:58:54.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}请停车，先生\N{\rENG}Monsieur, aretes vous!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.95,0:58:56.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}过了红绿灯您就停，我去坐地铁\N{\rENG}Non, non, c'est bon, aux feux-la!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.28,0:58:58.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,别，别停，继续开…\N{\rENG}No, don't. No, no, keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.85,0:59:02.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,听我说，我真的很高兴…谢谢你，请继续开…\N{\rENG}Listen, I'm just so happy...Thank you, just keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.62,0:59:04.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啦\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.66,0:59:09.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,听我说，我真得很高兴能跟你在一起\N{\rENG}Look, I'm just so happy,all right, to be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.56,0:59:12.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真得很高兴你没有忘记我\N{\rENG}I am. I'm so glad you didn't forget about me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.13,0:59:15.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，我没有，而这吓坏我了，知道吗？\N{\rENG}No, I didn't.And it pisses me off, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.04,0:59:19.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,你到巴黎来，给我带来浪漫，但却结了婚\N{\rENG}You come here to Paris,all romantic, and married.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.87,0:59:21.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,去死吧你！\N{\rENG}Okay? Screw you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.17,0:59:24.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要误会我，我并没有想要占有你\N{\rENG}Don't get me wrong,I'm not trying to get you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.71,0:59:27.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只不过想把自己嫁出去\N{\rENG}I mean, all I need is a married man.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.81,0:59:31.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个问题很复杂，这甚至不仅仅是关于你\N{\rENG}There's been so much water under the bridge, it's not even about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.32,0:59:33.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有那段过去的时光，那段永远不会再回来的时光！\N{\rENG}It's about that moment in time that's forever gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.99,0:59:36.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说了这么多，但你却根本不记得我们做过爱\N{\rENG}You say that, but you didn't even remember having sex, so....
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.06,0:59:39.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我当然记得\N{\rENG}Of course I remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.06,0:59:43.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你记得？ - 没错！\N{\rENG}- You did?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.66,0:59:47.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 女人总喜欢这么掩饰自己  - 是吗？\N{\rENG}- Women pretend things like that.  - They do?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.23,0:59:51.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,我应该说什么呢？说我记得公园里的红酒…\N{\rENG}What was I supposed to say?That I remember the wine in the park...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.37,0:59:54.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,…说我们我们一起看着星星落下太阳升起！\N{\rENG}...and us looking up at the stars fading away as the sun came up?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.04,0:59:58.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们做了两次爱，你这混蛋！\N{\rENG}We had sex twice, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.81,1:00:03.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啦，你知道吗，我真得很高兴看到你\N{\rENG}All right, you know what,I'm just happy to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.82,1:00:07.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,即使你已变得易怒和神经质\N{\rENG}Even if you've become an angry,manic-depressive activist...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.39,1:00:10.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还是很喜欢你，我还是愿意跟你待在一起！\N{\rENG}...I still like you,I still enjoy being around you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.56,1:00:15.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也是，对不起，我不知道怎么了，我只是…\N{\rENG}And I feel the same. I'm sorry.I don't know what happened, I just....
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.10,1:00:18.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我需要发泄，我…  - 没事\N{\rENG}- I had to let it all out.  - Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.73,1:00:21.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的感情生活太不顺利了\N{\rENG}I'm so miserable in my love life,in my relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.53,1:00:24.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我总是装作…好像我不在意它\N{\rENG}I always act as...Like, you know, I'm detached.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.87,1:00:28.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我真得痛不欲生，因为麻木而痛不欲生\N{\rENG}But I'm dying inside.I'm dying because I'm so numb.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.21,1:00:31.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不能感受到伤心和兴奋，我也不会感到苦涩，我只是…\N{\rENG}I don't feel pain or excitement,I'm not even bitter, I'm just....
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.11,1:00:34.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以为只有你痛不欲生吗？\N{\rENG}You think you're the one dying inside?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.95,1:00:39.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的生活每时每刻全像是地狱\N{\rENG}My life is 24/7 bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.35,1:00:40.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 对不起…  - 不要…\N{\rENG}- I'm sorry.  - No, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.85,1:00:43.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我唯一的快乐就是跟我儿子出去\N{\rENG}I mean, the only happiness I get is when I'm out with my son.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.92,1:00:45.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我去找了婚姻咨询\N{\rENG}I've been to marriage counseling...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.76,1:00:48.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,我做了我从来没想过我会做的事\N{\rENG}...I've done things I never thought I would have to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.56,1:00:51.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,我点了蜡烛，买了自助读物，女性内衣…\N{\rENG}I've lit candles,bought self-help books, lingerie.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.66,1:00:54.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 蜡烛有用吗？ - 有个鬼用！\N{\rENG}- Did the candles help?  - Hell, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.23,1:00:56.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没法用她想要的方式爱她\N{\rENG}I don't love her the way she needs to be loved...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.90,1:01:01.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,…我甚至根本看不到我们的未来，但当我看到我的小儿子\N{\rENG}...and I don't even see a future for us,but then I look at my little boy...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.51,1:01:04.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,…坐在桌子的对面，我就觉得我愿意承受一切折磨…\N{\rENG}...sitting across from me,and I think I'd suffer any torture...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.08,1:01:07.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,…只要能跟他一起度过他生命中的每一刻\N{\rENG}...to be with him for all the minutes of his life.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.61,1:01:09.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一刻也不想缺\N{\rENG}I don't want to miss out on one.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.65,1:01:13.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我的家里没有欢笑，没有快乐\N{\rENG}But then, there's no joy or laughter in my home, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.15,1:01:17.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我不希望他在这样的环境中长大  - 没有欢笑？那可太糟了\N{\rENG}- I don't want him growing up in that.  - No laughter? That's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.02,1:01:19.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的父母在一起已经有三十五年了\N{\rENG}My parents have been together 35 years...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.13,1:01:22.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,而即使他们吵架之后，他们还会笑得一样开心\N{\rENG}...and even when they fight they end up laughing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.63,1:01:26.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不想变成那种人，在五十二岁时离了婚…\N{\rENG}I don't want to be one of those people who are getting divorced at 52...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.60,1:01:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,…落着泪，承认从来就没有爱过自己的伴侣…\N{\rENG}...and falling down into tears, admitting they never really loved their spouse...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.17,1:01:36.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,…感觉自己的生活好像完全被吸尘器吸走一样，一片空虚\N{\rENG}...and they feel their life has been sucked up into a vacuum cleaner.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.44,1:01:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也想拥有美好的生活，我也希望她拥有美好的生活\N{\rENG}You know, I want a great life.I want her to have a great life...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.21,1:01:42.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是她应得的！\N{\rENG}...she deserves that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.62,1:01:45.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,但现在我们只是假装维系着婚姻，责任\N{\rENG}But we're just living in the pretense of a marriage, responsibility...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.12,1:01:50.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,…过着那种人们觉得你该过的日子\N{\rENG}...you know, all these ideas of how people are supposed to live.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.82,1:01:55.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后，我…我做了一个梦\N{\rENG}But then I... I have these dreams....
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.20,1:01:58.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么梦？\N{\rENG}What dreams?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.73,1:02:02.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,我做了一个梦\N{\rENG}I have these dreams,you know, that...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.70,1:02:04.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,…梦见我站在月台上\N{\rENG}...I'm standing on a platform...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.01,1:02:09.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而你不停的坐火车经过\N{\rENG}...and you keep going by on a train...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.31,1:02:13.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,…你就是不停的经过，经过，经过\N{\rENG}...and you go by, and you go by,and you go by, you go by.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.88,1:02:15.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后我被吓醒，浑身冷汗\N{\rENG}And I wake up with the fucking sweats.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.95,1:02:18.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后我又做了一个梦…\N{\rENG}And then I have this other dream...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.45,1:02:22.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,…梦见你怀孕了，在床上躺在我身边，一丝不挂…\N{\rENG}...where you're pregnant in bed beside me naked...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.49,1:02:26.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,…而我非常非常想要抚摸你，但你跟我说不要，然后你就把头别过去\N{\rENG}...and I want so badly to touch you, but you tell me not to and you look away.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.46,1:02:30.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后我…我还是抚摸了你…\N{\rENG}And I... And I touch you anyway...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.10,1:02:35.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,…摸你的脚踝那里，你的皮肤是那样的柔软，使得我在哭泣中醒来\N{\rENG}...right on your ankle, and your skin is so soft that I wake up in sobs, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.34,1:02:39.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的妻子就坐在那里，看着我，我却觉得她离我万里之遥\N{\rENG}My wife is there looking at me,and I feel I'm a million miles from her.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.97,1:02:44.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道那不对劲，我…\N{\rENG}And I know that there's something wrong, that I...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.18,1:02:46.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,天啊！我不能再这样活下去了…\N{\rENG}God, that I can't keep living like this...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.35,1:02:48.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,…爱的意义一定不仅仅是责任\N{\rENG}...that there's gotta be more to love than commitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.08,1:02:51.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,但然后我又想，也许我已经不相信…\N{\rENG}But then I think that I might have given up...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.05,1:02:53.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,…浪漫的爱情了\N{\rENG}...on the whole idea of romantic love.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.12,1:02:57.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可能早已经不信了\N{\rENG}That I might have put it to bed that...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.59,1:03:00.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,自从那天我在那里没有见你\N{\rENG}That day when you weren't there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.53,1:03:03.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想，我可能就开始消沉了\N{\rENG}You know, I think I might have done that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.53,1:03:06.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你为什么要和我说这些？\N{\rENG}Why are you telling me all this?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.60,1:03:11.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,对不起，我不知道，我…我应该…\N{\rENG}I'm sorry. I don't know.I'm... I should....
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.01,1:03:14.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不应该说的\N{\rENG}I shouldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.11,1:03:16.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道，太奇怪了\N{\rENG}You know, it's so weird.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.88,1:03:20.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,人们总是觉得自己是唯一痛苦的人\N{\rENG}People think they are the only one going through tough times.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.11,1:03:25.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,当我读那些文章的时候，我觉得你的生活是完美的\N{\rENG}I mean, when I read the article,I thought your life was perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.72,1:03:29.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,有太太，孩子，出版了自己的作品\N{\rENG}A wife, a kid, published author.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.26,1:03:33.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在看来你的生活比我还糟！\N{\rENG}But your personal life is more of a mess than mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.79,1:03:36.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,对不起！\N{\rENG}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.30,1:03:38.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,起码有些方面还过得去\N{\rENG}Well, I'm glad it's good for something.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.75,1:03:39.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}噢，先生，就是那儿！\N{\rENG}Oh, monsieur, c'est la!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.05,1:03:42.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}把车停到那个通道里就行了\N{\rENG}Rentrez dans la passe-la.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.13,1:03:45.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这里就是你住的地方？ - 没错\N{\rENG}- This is where you live?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.31,1:03:50.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,那现在看到我的生活比你还糟，觉得舒服点了吧？\N{\rENG}So you're just relieved that I'm in even more deep shit than you are?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.64,1:03:52.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，你让我感觉好多了\N{\rENG}Yes, you've made me feel better.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.68,1:03:54.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，那就好，我很高兴…\N{\rENG}Oh, good, I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.05,1:03:57.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，我真的希望你的生活可以更好\N{\rENG}No, I really wish you the best.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.65,1:04:01.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不会因为自己无法有良好的感情，或是美好的家庭\N{\rENG}It's not because I'm incapable of having a good relationship or a family...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.49,1:04:03.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,就想要别人也跟我一样不开心\N{\rENG}...that I wish everyone to be doomed like me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.79,1:04:06.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道你总有一天会成为…一个伟大的母亲的！\N{\rENG}I'm sure you'd make... Be a great mom someday.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.33,1:04:07.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真的？你真的这么认为？ - 没错\N{\rENG}- Really? You think so?  - Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.99,1:04:11.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,只要服一些抗忧郁药，你就行了！\N{\rENG}...a few antidepressants, you know,you'll do great.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.93,1:04:14.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 喊停！ - 停！\N{\rENG}- Okay, say stop.  - Stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.20,1:04:17.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好啦  - 准备好了吗？好啦\N{\rENG}- Okay.  - You ready? Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.08,1:04:32.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我想试一下  - 什么？\N{\rENG}- So I want to try something.  - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.72,1:04:39.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想看看你是会保持原样还是会融化\N{\rENG}I want to see if you stay together or if you dissolve into molecules.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.13,1:04:42.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,我融化了吗？\N{\rENG}How am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.23,1:04:44.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,保持原样！\N{\rENG}Still here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.33,1:04:46.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,很好，我喜欢住在这儿\N{\rENG}Good. I like being here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.37,1:04:51.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是你的公寓吗？\N{\rENG}Is this your apartment?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.14,1:04:53.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，我住在那里\N{\rENG}No, I live down there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.01,1:04:56.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那里？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- Down there?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.41,1:04:58.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,先生，我想送她进家门\N{\rENG}Monsieur, I'm gonna walk her to her door.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.55,1:05:04.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}他要送我进家门\N{\rENG}Il va m'accompagner...a la porte.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.99,1:05:09.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,太不可思议了！\N{\rENG}This is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.49,1:05:12.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这就是你住的地方？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- This is where you live?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.36,1:05:15.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你搬来这里多久了？ - 四年了\N{\rENG}- How long have you been here?  - Four years.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.13,1:05:19.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那告诉我…  - 什么？\N{\rENG}- So tell me....  - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.43,1:05:21.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,你讲的那些你的梦，是真的吗？\N{\rENG}Is it all true about your dreams...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.27,1:05:24.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,还是只是为了骗我上床？\N{\rENG}...or did you say that to hopefully get in my pants?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.20,1:05:25.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然只是骗你上床啦！\N{\rENG}I said that to get in your pants.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.94,1:05:28.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这是我的惯用伎俩  - 哦，有用吗？\N{\rENG}- I use that all the time.  - Oh, okay. Does it work?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.67,1:05:31.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯，有时候\N{\rENG}You know. Sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.71,1:05:36.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是我的猫咪，哦，太可爱了，看看它\N{\rENG}Here's my kitty. Oh, so cute.Look at him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.38,1:05:38.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我喜欢他的什么吗？\N{\rENG}You know what I love about this cat?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.38,1:05:40.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,每天早上我带他下来\N{\rENG}Every morning I bring him to the courtyard...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.89,1:05:45.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,…每一个早晨，他都会像是第一次来到这个院子一样！\N{\rENG}...and every single morning he looks at everything like it was the first time.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.76,1:05:49.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,每个角落，每棵树，每棵植物\N{\rENG}Every corner, every tree, every plant.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.03,1:05:52.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,都用他可爱的小鼻子去闻闻\N{\rENG}Smells everything with his little cute nose.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.67,1:05:56.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,我太喜欢他了！\N{\rENG}Oh, I love my kitty. I love my kitty.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.97,1:05:59.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 他叫什么？ - 奇\N{\rENG}- What's his name?  - Che.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.54,1:06:02.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,奇？\N{\rENG}Che?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.08,1:06:06.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 怎么了？ - 听起来像共产党员\N{\rENG}- What?  - Commie.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.95,1:06:10.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，“奇”在阿根廷是用来打招呼用的！\N{\rENG}No, "che" in argentina means "hey."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.12,1:06:13.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真的？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- Okay.  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.72,1:06:17.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，宝贝，哦，好啊，好啊\N{\rENG}Oh, baby. Oh, yes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.79,1:06:24.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们晚上有个聚餐！超好玩的！\N{\rENG}We're having a little party.It's so much fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.05,1:06:27.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}你为晚餐准备了什么好东西？\N{\rENG}Qu'est-ce que vous avez fait bon pour ce soir?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.85,1:06:28.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}塔布雷色拉\N{\rENG}Un taboule!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.85,1:06:30.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}我过五分钟下来\N{\rENG}Je vais descendre dans cinq minutes!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.95,1:06:31.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}你好\N{\rENG}Salut!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.20,1:06:33.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}你好\N{\rENG}Salut!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.55,1:06:36.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那…  - 那\N{\rENG}- So....  - So.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.35,1:06:39.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}这是谁？帅哥啊！\N{\rENG}C'est qui celui-la? Il est mignon!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.45,1:06:41.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}他和我们共进晚餐吗？ - {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}不，他要赶飞机\N{\rENG}- Il mange avec nous?  - Non, il prend l'avion.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.45,1:06:44.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}可惜他尝不到我的拿手菜了\N{\rENG}Tant pis! Il ne goutera pas mes paton pois chiches.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.45,1:06:45.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}他为什么不留下吃晚饭？\N{\rENG}Pour-quo'il ne mange pas avec nous?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.95,1:06:48.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}他不喜欢你的短裤！\N{\rENG}Il n'aime pas ton short!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.15,1:06:50.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}我的短裤怎么了？\N{\rENG}Mais qu'es-ce qu'il a mon short?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.83,1:06:57.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗？我在想，你可以唱一首你的歌给我听吗？\N{\rENG}You know what? I was thinking,would you play me one of your songs?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.46,1:06:59.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你会错过你的班机的！ - 不，不会的！\N{\rENG}- You're gonna miss your flight.  - I won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.80,1:07:02.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我坐在候机厅也只不过是读一个小时的报纸\N{\rENG}I'm gonna be in the airport for over an hour, reading...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.87,1:07:05.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,…所以还是听你唱一首歌给我听吧\N{\rENG}...wishing you'd played me one of your songs.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.00,1:07:08.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,一首？好吧，不过很短的\N{\rENG}One song? Okay, but quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.37,1:07:10.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.51,1:07:18.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我太喜欢这老楼梯了\N{\rENG}God, I love these old staircases.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.02,1:07:59.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 拿着！ - 什么，让我来？\N{\rENG}- Hold this.  - What, for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.49,1:08:01.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,嘿，小家伙\N{\rENG}Hey there, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.59,1:08:04.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,奇\N{\rENG}Che.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.18,1:08:19.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你想喝点茶吗？ - 好啊\N{\rENG}- Would you like some tea?  - Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.45,1:08:22.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,哇\N{\rENG}Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.08,1:08:26.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 甘菊茶好吗？ - 嗯，很好\N{\rENG}- Is chamomile okay?  - Yeah. Great.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.75,1:08:29.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}谢谢！ - 乱？{\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[谐音]{\rCHS}\N{\rENG}- Merci.  - Messy?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.19,1:08:32.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你觉得我的房间很乱？ - 不不不，我是说谢谢\N{\rENG}- You think my apartment is messy?  - No, no. Merci.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.09,1:08:36.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\fs45\c&H9AD1DD&}[法语]{\rCHS}非常感谢  - 哦，谢谢\N{\rENG}- Merci beaucoup.  - Ah, merci.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.83,1:08:40.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想告诉你，你的法语进步很多\N{\rENG}I meant to tell you,your French has improved a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.73,1:08:42.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真的吗？ - 没错！\N{\rENG}- Really?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.23,1:08:44.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,你已经完全掌握这门语言了\N{\rENG}Yeah, you've really mastered the language.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.60,1:08:48.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，那你想要唱哪首歌？\N{\rENG}All right, all right, what song are you gonna play me?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.94,1:08:53.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,不行，我唱不了，这太丢人了\N{\rENG}No, I can't. It's too embarrassing.It's been...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.05,1:08:57.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,哇！不行！我这么费劲上来就是为了这个，你不能这样坑我\N{\rENG}Whoa. No way. No way. I came up here,you cannot crap out on me now.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.92,1:08:59.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,就一首，随便那首都行\N{\rENG}One song. Anything will be great.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.15,1:09:01.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,但你会笑我的\N{\rENG}But listen, you're gonna laugh at me.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.12,1:09:03.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你这么觉得？ - 是的！\N{\rENG}- You think so?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.86,1:09:05.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,放心，我不会的\N{\rENG}I doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.59,1:09:09.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.16,1:09:12.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,你想听什么？我有…\N{\rENG}What do you want to hear? I have....
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.73,1:09:15.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,我有三首英文歌\N{\rENG}I have three songs in English.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.23,1:09:16.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,一首是唱我的猫的\N{\rENG}One's about my cat...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.77,1:09:20.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,…一首是唱我的前男友，呃，前前男友…\N{\rENG}...one's about my ex-boyfriend...Well, ex-ex-boyfriend...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.01,1:09:23.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,…还有一首是…\N{\rENG}...and there's one about....
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.91,1:09:27.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,是首华尔兹\N{\rENG}Well, it's just a little waltz.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.45,1:09:29.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,华尔兹？\N{\rENG}A waltz? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.78,1:09:31.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那就唱华尔兹吧  - 好吧\N{\rENG}- Play the waltz.  - Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.12,1:09:34.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,我已经很久没弹吉他了，你确定你想听吗？\N{\rENG}I haven't played it in a while.You sure?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.89,1:09:39.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.16,1:09:42.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，华尔兹\N{\rENG}All right, the waltz.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.67,1:09:59.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我唱首华尔兹\N{\rENG}Let me sing you a waltz
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.34,1:10:04.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,无从讲起，从我的心底\N{\rENG}Out of nowhere, out of my thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.28,1:10:08.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我唱首华尔兹\N{\rENG}Let me sing you a waltz
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.99,1:10:12.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,唱那次一夜缠绵\N{\rENG}About this one-night stand
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.96,1:10:19.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,那晚，你是我的\N{\rENG}You were, for me, that night
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.83,1:10:25.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是我生命中的全部梦想\N{\rENG}Everything I always dreamt of in life
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.94,1:10:29.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,但你已经不在了\N{\rENG}But now you're gone
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.64,1:10:33.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,你去了很远的地方\N{\rENG}You are far-gone
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.88,1:10:39.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,你那的雨中小岛\N{\rENG}All the way to your island of rain
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.72,1:10:45.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,对你来说，那只是一夜情\N{\rENG}It was, for you, just a one-night thing
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.76,1:10:48.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,对我来说却远远不止\N{\rENG}But you were much more to me
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.96,1:10:51.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想让你知道\N{\rENG}Just so you know
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.70,1:10:55.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不管别人怎样说\N{\rENG}I don 't care what they say
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.87,1:11:00.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道你对我的意义\N{\rENG}I know what you meant For me that day
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.01,1:11:05.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只想再来一次\N{\rENG}I just want another try
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.01,1:11:11.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只想再来一夜\N{\rENG}I just want another night
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.25,1:11:18.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,即使这看起来毫无意义\N{\rENG}Even if it doesn 't seem quite right
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.42,1:11:22.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,但你对我来说\N{\rENG}You meant, for me, much more
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.59,1:11:26.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,要比任何人都更重要\N{\rENG}Than anyone I've met before
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.10,1:11:33.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,和你共度的一夜啊，小杰西\N{\rENG}One single night with you, little Jesse
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.61,1:11:38.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,比得上和他人的一千个夜晚\N{\rENG}Is worth a thousand with anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.78,1:11:43.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没有痛苦，亲亲\N{\rENG}I have no bitterness, my sweet
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.52,1:11:48.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我永远不会忘记这一夜缠绵\N{\rENG}I'll never forget this one-night thing
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.75,1:11:54.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,即使明天我在他人怀中\N{\rENG}Even tomorrow, in other arms
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.06,1:12:01.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的心还会随你而去，直到生命尽头\N{\rENG}My heart will stay yours until I die
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.27,1:12:10.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我唱一首华尔兹\N{\rENG}Let me sing you a waltz
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.24,1:12:15.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,无从讲起，从我的心底\N{\rENG}Out of nowhere, out of my blues
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.45,1:12:20.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我唱一首华尔兹\N{\rENG}Let me sing you a waltz
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.59,1:12:25.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,唱那可爱的一夜情\N{\rENG}About this lovely one-night stand
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.87,1:12:46.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不要停，再来一首，求你了  - 不行，说好了的！\N{\rENG}- No, one more! Please, please.  - No! It was our deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.71,1:12:49.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,一首，就一首，别，别\N{\rENG}One... One song. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.38,1:12:51.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,你可以喝完你的茶再…\N{\rENG}You can have your tea and then....
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.36,1:12:59.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好吧，我问你个问题  - 什么？\N{\rENG}- All right, let me ask you one question.  - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.89,1:13:03.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是不是每次不管谁来就在歌词里换个名字？\N{\rENG}Do you just plug that name in for every guy that comes up here?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.80,1:13:05.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然了\N{\rENG}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.30,1:13:09.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以为呢？我是写给你的？你疯了吗？\N{\rENG}What do you think, that I wrote the song about you? Are you nuts?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.74,1:13:16.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是你吗？小对眼塞琳？\N{\rENG}Is this you? Little cross-eyed Celine?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.31,1:13:18.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是的，那张很好笑  - 可爱\N{\rENG}- Yes. That's funny.  - Cute.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.25,1:13:23.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这就是你的祖母？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- Is that your grandmother?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.42,1:13:27.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,哇\N{\rENG}Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.89,1:13:30.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你要加点蜂蜜吗？ - 好的\N{\rENG}- You want some honey?  - Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.67,1:14:22.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,你听过尼娜·西蒙的演唱会吗？\N{\rENG}Did you ever see Nina Simone in concert?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.18,1:14:25.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有，不敢相信她已经不在了\N{\rENG}No, I never did.I can't believe she's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.04,1:14:27.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道，太让人伤心了\N{\rENG}I know, it's so sad.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.68,1:14:30.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rENG}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.28,1:14:32.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,真热\N{\rENG}It's hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.39,1:14:37.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,我听过她两次演唱会\N{\rENG}I saw her twice in concert.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.82,1:14:40.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,她真棒！\N{\rENG}She was so great.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.33,1:14:43.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是她的歌里我最喜欢的几首之一\N{\rENG}That's one of my favorite songs of hers.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.21,1:15:00.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,她太棒了！\N{\rENG}She was so great.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.45,1:15:04.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,她在演唱会里太有趣了\N{\rENG}She was so funny in concert too.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.92,1:15:09.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,她会…她会在一首歌唱到一半时的时候\N{\rENG}She would... She would be right in the middle of a song and then...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.25,1:15:11.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,…你知道吗，停下来…\N{\rENG}...you know, stop...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.29,1:15:15.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,…从钢琴边起身，一直走到舞台边上\N{\rENG}...and walk from the piano all the way to the edge of the stage.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.53,1:15:17.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,像这样，非常慢的\N{\rENG}Like, really slowly.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.83,1:15:24.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后她开始对观众中的某人说话\N{\rENG}And she'd start talking to someone in the audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.30,1:15:27.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，耶，哦，耶\N{\rENG}"Oh, yeah, baby. Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.44,1:15:30.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也爱你\N{\rENG}I love you too."
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.11,1:15:35.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后她又走回去，不急不忙的，\N{\rENG}And then she'd walk back.Take her time, no hurry, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.75,1:15:39.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,她的大屁股真可爱\N{\rENG}She had that big, cute ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.38,1:15:40.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,她就这么慢慢挪着\N{\rENG}She would move.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.65,1:15:47.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后就走回钢琴旁再唱一段\N{\rENG}And then she would go back to the piano and play some more, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.99,1:15:50.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后她会，我也不知道…\N{\rENG}And then she would, I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.83,1:15:53.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,…一首歌唱了一半又唱另外一首\N{\rENG}...just start another song in the middle of another.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.50,1:15:57.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,你懂吗，好像，又停下，然后这样\N{\rENG}You know, like,stop again, and be like:
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.47,1:16:01.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,那边那位，你能挪挪那电扇吗\N{\rENG}"You over there,can you move that fan.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.37,1:16:04.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,你真可爱\N{\rENG}You're cute.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.53,1:16:27.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，耶\N{\rENG}Oh, yeah."
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.07,1:16:35.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,宝贝，你会错过你的班机的\N{\rENG}Baby, you are gonna miss that plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.68,1:16:38.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rENG}I know.

